title: sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, medium size is best.
Pack in large mouth jar. Fill jar with cold water and seal.
Let set at least 3 weeks.
To sweeten, open drain and wash pickles. 3 weeks.
Slice or chunk as preferred.
Pack in jar.
Add 2 cups of sugar.
If real dry, add 3 tablespoons of water and place in refrigerator for about 3 days. Shake jar several times, will dampen sugar.
Ready to eat.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape in rolls; wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet (350°) for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Brown beef and drain; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: normandy-style chicken(poulet saute' d' yuetot)
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Saute in oil.
Spread chopped apples in layer in bottom of casserole.
When the chicken is half cooked, remove from skillet and place in casserole on top of apples. Deglaze skillet with 1/4 cup apple liquid.
Add to chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli on bottom of pan.
Put chicken on top; mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Mix and sift together dry ingredients.
Separate eggs; beat yolks and add milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add cooled melted shortening, vanilla and nuts.
Fold in egg whites beaten stiff. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: veggie-macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and rinse.
Add margarine, eggs and milk. Boil vegetables (5 minutes).
Add to macaroni mixture.
Add cheese and mix well.
Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole, reserve some cheese for topping.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Moisten with real mayonnaise.
Add seasoned salt, garlic and onion powder or salt to taste.

title: sweet meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together, form meatloaf and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles; brown ground beef and onion until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Add noodles, corn, soup, sour cream and pimentos; mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: salsa
directions: Mix in large kettle; bring to a boil.
Reduce; simmer 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.
Stir occasionally.
Right before 1 1/2 hours are up, bring to boil again and put in jars and seal.
Store in cool place.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, being sure to add lemon juice last. Pour into graham cracker crusts; keep refrigerated.
(Let Cool Whip soften before using.)

title: white lasagna
directions: Mix meat, soup, milk, black olives and spices.
Layer noodles, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers 3 times.
Cover; let stand overnight, then add 1 cup boiling water.
Sprinkle over the top a mixture of the Rice Chex, melted margarine and Parmesan cheese. Cook in an 8 x 12-inch pan at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef, breadcrumbs, salt, nutmeg, onion, milk, water and egg.
Mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in hot oil until browned.
Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice; add to meatballs and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: seafood herb tart
directions: Spread dough on bottom and halfway up sides of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with tomato, green pepper, onion, Parmesan cheese and Crab Delights.
Mix eggs, water, mustard and seasoning in small bowl.
Pour over Crab Delights.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes or until eggs are set and puffed in center. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into cubes.
Cook in water until tender. Drain.
Add salt and pepper to eggplant.
Saute onions in butter until soft.
Mash tomatoes, mix with onions and combine with eggplant.
Beat in eggs and bread crumbs.
Grease casserole.
Spoon in eggplant.
Pour milk over top until covered.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly all the way through.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in apples.
Pour into 2 ungreased loaf pans or 4 mini loaf pans or muffin pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove immediately from pans.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Then wrap in foil while warm.
Freezes well.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In large salad bowl, shred head of lettuce and fill the bowl half full.
Then spread evenly over the lettuce in layers the following:
celery, green pepper, onion and peas.
Spread Miracle Whip evenly over the layer of peas.
Sprinkle sugar over the Miracle Whip and top with the Cheddar cheese.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap and leave in the refrigerator overnight.
Just before serving, garnish with tomato wedges.

title: aunt c's clusters
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, blend well.
Pour over cornflakes and mix to make sure all cornflakes are covered.
Drop by teaspoonfuls
onto waxed paper.
Leave until set.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Fill pie crust with fruit.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes, until firm.

title: sweet corn chowder with shrimp and red pepper
directions: Heat the oil for 1 minute in a large saucepan over moderate heat.
Add the onion; saute, stirring until limp, about 5 minutes. Add the potato, bay leaf, marjoram, nutmeg and stock; bring to a boil.
Lower the heat to moderate; cover and cook at a gentle boil until the potato is just tender, about 10 minutes.
Add the cream-style corn, corn kernels, milk and black pepper; bring to a boil.
Lower the heat to moderate.
Add the red pepper and shrimp; boil, gently uncovered, until the shrimp are just cooked through, about 3 minutes.
Remove the bay leaf.
Serves 6.

title: northern potato salad
directions: Boil eggs and potatoes.
Let cool and peel.
Then cut up potatoes in medium size cubes and cut eggs into very small pieces. Then cut celery into small pieces.
Slice radishes very thin. Put all of these together and add salt, pepper, paprika, mustard, vinegar and Miracle Whip.
Mix together.
Chill 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch glass baking pan.
Beat eggs and all wet ingredients.
Once mixed, add all dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Pour in baking pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: curry paste for meat
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add anchovy paste and vinegar and mix well. Store in small airtight container in refrigerator. (Keeps several weeks.)

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken parts, skin side down, in baking pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Turn and bake 20 minutes more.
Stir in 1 can cream of mushroom soup until smooth. Top chicken with soup and bake 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: saucy chicken stir-fry
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook carrots, zucchini and mushrooms (may use other vegetables).
In bowl, stir together cornstarch, chicken broth and soy sauce until smooth. Gradually stir in vegetables.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: wedding soup
directions: Stew chicken 2 1/2 to 3 hours until meat falls off bones.
Make ground meat into small meatballs and add to deboned chicken and broth.
Cook spinach separately.
Add cooked spinach to chicken, broth and meatballs.
Cook until meatballs are done (approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Whip eggs until fluffy; mix in cheese and whip some more.
Pour slowly into hot soup mixture.
If broth is not strong enough, add a couple of bouillon cubes (chicken).
Season to taste.
Tastes better the second day.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cranberry sauce until smooth and add pineapple, apple, pecans and celery.
Stir until mixed. Refrigerate.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in a heavy Dutch oven.
Stir thoroughly from bottom.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
(In a crock-pot, cook for 3 1/2 to 5 hours.)

title: frozen layer dessert
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in crumbs.
Reserve 1 tablespoon for garnish and pat crumbs on bottom of buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine pie filling, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth. Spread into prepared pan.
Top with whipping cream and reserved crumbs.
Freeze for 3 hours.
Serves 9.

title: pickled beets
directions: Scald the vinegar with the sugar and pickling spice.
Add the water and the beets.
Cover and let stand at least one day before using.

title: creamy dressing-lettuce
directions: Cook ingredients until thick.
Add ham or bacon (cut up), and dice a couple of hard boiled eggs and add.
Put in container and use as needed.

title: a great sangria
directions: Add sugar to cold water and bring to a boil to dissolve sugar quickly.
Remove from heat and add sliced fruits.
Cover and let stand for about four hours.

title: michigan meat balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and form into balls.
Roll in flour. Brown slowly.
Pour the soup and water over and simmer 20 minutes.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender.
Combine all ingredients except paprika and 1/2 cup cheese. Blend well. Pour into greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and paprika. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: herbed vegetable puff
directions: Saute broccoli and carrots in margarine until crisp-tender; stir in tomatoes.
Place in four 8 ounce baking dishes.
Beat egg whites and salt until stiff peaks form.
Fold in combined remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture evenly over vegetables. Broil 3 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: king pie
directions: Combine and put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken saute with garlic
directions: Heat butter and oil in saute pan or cast-iron casserole. Brown chicken pieces.
Add garlic and shallots.
Saute for 10 minutes or until skins of garlic are lightly colored.
Season liberally with salt and pepper. Add the wine.
Cover, reduce heat and cook gently for 30 minutes. When meat is done, uncover and turn heat on high.
Boil this, stirring constantly, until liquid evaporates.
Bring saute pan to the table and serve chicken pieces with the garlic cloves.
Eat the garlic with the chicken, first biting into each clove so that you can slide the tough skin off and discard it on your plate. The taste of the garlic is exquisitely subtle.
You can also add broccoli and Brussels sprouts (quartered or halved) to this.
Can be served with rice or pasta.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients; spread in bottom of dish.

title: raspberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve the jello and salt in boiling water.
Add 2 packages partly thawed frozen raspberries.
Stir until completely thawed. Chill until jello partly sets.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix 5 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon and sprinkle over sliced apples.
Let stand 1/2 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup peanut butter and 1 jar Marshmallow Creme. Pour into buttered pan.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
(Save 1 cup for crumbs on top of cake.)
To remaining flour mixture, add molasses, water, baking soda and oil.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 1/4-inch pan. Spread 1 cup flour mixture on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: katie's ritz pie
directions: Crush Ritz crackers and combine with walnuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar to egg whites and blend.
Fold egg whites into nut mixture and add vanilla.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes (until golden brown).
Cool, then refrigerate.
When ready to serve, whip heavy cream and spread over pie.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Mix in egg and flavorings.
Add blended dry ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface and cut with a cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and, if desired, decorate with colored sprinkles, red hots, etc.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: no cook, never fail fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine together in top of double boiler. Sift sugar and cocoa together until thoroughly mixed and no lumps remain.
This is very important.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth; cook and stir until mixture boils.
Cook one minute; set aside.
Brown chops in oil; season with additional salt and pepper, if desired.

title: carrot salad or copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender; drain well. Mix in remaining ingredients while carrots are hot. Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours. Serve cold.

title: sour beef and potato dumplings
directions: Marinate meat for several days in vinegar, water and pickling spices (put spices in a spice bag; can use piece of cheesecloth). Place meat and juice in pot and add remaining ingredients and enough water to cover.
Cook for several hours until meat is fork-tender.
(Can be cooked in crock-pot.)
Cook and drain potatoes.
Mash with egg and add flour until potatoes can be formed into balls.
Use hands.
Drop into boiling, salted water and cook until balls rise to top.
Serve with sour beef.

title: he-man biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco; add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
You don't need to let them rise.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Store remainder of dough in airtight container.
You can take dough out of refrigerator and cook.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.
Cook at 400°
until done.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; chop onions and cook along with hamburger. When hamburger is cooked, add tomato paste and chili sauce. Simmer for a few minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix
shortening and sugars together until creamed;
add eggs and mix until fluffy.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla to mixture
and beat about 1 minute.
Mix flour, soda and salt together; then
add
to
mixture
a
little
at a time.
Don't grease pans.
Make	into little balls and press down.
Bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix together and place in tube or loaf pan to mold.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut graham crackers in half and lay out on a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Sprinkle crackers with nuts.
In a medium size saucepan, melt margarine; add sugar and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Spoon mixture over crackers and bake 10 minutes.
Remove immediately with a spatula onto aluminum foil.
Let cool.
These freeze well.

title: hamburger steak in mushroom gravy
directions: Season ground beef with salt and pepper; form into patties. Cook over medium heat until done.
Drain most of the excess grease from the pan.
Pour soup into skillet with patties and add mushrooms.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Boil chicken in garlic water until cooked. Cool; dice in large pieces and set aside. Peel and dice potatoes in large pieces. Peel and diced onions. Cook potatoes, onions and corn in chicken broth. Add chicken and milk.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crush wafers; melt margarine.
Mix well and pat firmly in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill in freezer.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; stir in milk and undrained strawberries.
Mix in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Stir until mixed well.
Take dish out, then pour mixture over, spreading evenly.
Chill 4 to 6 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: new reduced fat peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat peanut butter and margarine until creamy. Beat in sugars, egg, soda, baking powder and vanilla until well blended.
Mix in flour thoroughly.
Form 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet, using a fork dipped in flour to mash flat.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes until light brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: different dessert
directions: Soak marshmallows in 1/2 cup cream.
Mix all ingredients together; form into a roll.
Roll in crumbs.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in slices.
Serve with whipped cream. Top with a maraschino cherry.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Mix together pimento, onions, water chestnuts, mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over peas and mix well. Refrigerate!

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into patties.
Fry until golden brown.
Makes 6 patties.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Wash meat with cold
water,
cover
with cold water and bring to the boiling point.
(If
very salty, it may be soaked in
cold water for several hours before cooking.) Skim, cover the kettle and simmer until the meat is tender (4 to 5 hours).

title: pineapple pie
directions: Whip 1 can of Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip together.
Add pineapple.
Fill pie shells and chill 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate the Longhorn cheese, sharp cheese, chipped beef, eggs, onion, peppers and olives.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Then, if you like, roll in crushed nuts.
Let set up overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat, drain, and set aside.
Blend next 4 ingredients. Stir in meat, cheese and onion.
Add seasonings.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Can be made ahead of time.
Freeze before baking.

title: mexican orange cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Add egg and orange peel.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in flour, alternately with orange juice.
Roll dough on floured board to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into shapes or doughnut rounds.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: corn-n-chicken chowder
directions: Melt margarine in large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms and saute for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour. Gradually add milk, stirring with a whisk.
Add the potato, thyme, salt, pepper and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in shredded chicken and 2 T. green onions.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with 1 T. green onions.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Combine vinegar, oil and sugar. Mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in fridge for at least one hour before serving. Best if marinated 8 hours or overnight.

title: cheese biscuits(cheese straws)
directions: Mix cheese and margarine well.
Add flour and salt.
You may add 2 tablespoons of Crisco for crispness, if desired.
Roll into ball the size of a marble.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: banana custard
directions: Cook together until thick and remove from heat; add a little butter or margarine.
In a serving dish, layer custard and sliced banana.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Mix all of the ingredients, except ginger ale.
Finish filling gallon jug with water.
Shake.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 6 to 8 hours before serving; will be slushy.
Add ginger ale to 1 gallon of punch in punch bowl.
Makes 1 gallon.
Serves 20 people.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients adding garlic powder to taste; chill thoroughly.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mash bananas thoroughly and add the slightly thawed orange juice and lemonade.
Sprinkle sugar over mixture.
Add the pineapple juice, stirring well to dissolve the sugar.
Put mixture into a gallon milk container and fill with water; do not fill to the top of container.
Allow space for expansion during freezing. Freeze to a slush.
At serving time, cut off top of milk container to remove slush.
Place mixture in a 2-gallon punch bowl and add the ginger ale.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix together, then add 8 ounce Cool Whip. Mix well with pudding. Take graham crackers and layer in pan or baking dish. Add layer of mixture rotating cracker and mixture cover. Refrigerate for 6 to 8 hours. Place container of chocolate icing in microwave for 15 seconds, then spread over layers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: morning glory
directions: Mix all ingredients in large punch bowl.
Add club soda and plenty of crushed ice.
Serves 20.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Pour over cereal and nuts.
Then pour mixture into paper grocery bag with powdered sugar in it and shake.
Store in airtight container.

title: tasty-easy chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread over chicken parts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy apples
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add apples.
Add sugar.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove cover and cook on medium heat.
Stir often.	Total cooking time:
25 minutes.

title: traditional roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, egg, margarine and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured counter; knead for 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise in warm place 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down dough; divide and make crescent rolls.
Let rise 20 minutes on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: layered salad(overnight)
directions: Hard-boil eggs.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Cook peas and let cool while chopping vegetables.
Mix together sugar, salad dressing and garlic powder.
Layer in a large pan in order of recipe.

title: t. cakes
directions: Mix the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add the vanilla and stir real good.
Add flour until you can't stir.
Pour into a bowl of flour with hole in center.
Work with hands until dough is thick.
Roll out and cut cookies.
Put on 2 large, greased and floured cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or brown.
Put into plastic ice cream bucket that is airtight.
They will keep for 2 months.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread in a well greased 9 x 13 pan; batter will be stiff, pat down.
Mix remaining 3 ingredients and pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle reserved powdered sugar on for topping.

title: almond and orange salad
directions: Toast almonds in 350° oven approximately 8 minutes until golden brown.
In bowl, combine greens, celery, parsley and onion. Cover and chill 2 to 4 hours.
In jar, combine oil, vinegar, sugar and hot pepper seasoning.
Shake well; just before serving, toss greens with dressing.
Distribute oranges and almonds over top.
Serve at once.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a rectangular pan.
Layer in pan margarine, pecans and coconut.
Prepare cake mix and pour over mixture in pan.
Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Leave it thick. Drop by spoonfuls on cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook pasta.
In skillet, brown meat and add onion.
When nearly done, add mushrooms, green pepper and pepperoni.
Cook until done. Drain fat.
Add tomatoes and pizza sauce.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, add salt and simmer until slightly thickened.
Combine with pasta and put in a casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Beat egg whites very stiff; add sugar slowly, beating all the time.
Add salt and vanilla and last, fold in the chips.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil; drop cookies on sheet with a teaspoon.
Put cookies in oven; close door and slowly count to ten.
Turn oven off and leave until next morning. Do not open oven until ready to take cookies out the next morning.

title: vanessa's cheesy french bread
directions: Cream together softened butter and cream cheese.
Mix in oregano and parsley.
Spread on sliced bread.
Arrange olives on bread (optional).
Sprinkle with garlic salt, paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Wrap in foil with the top exposed.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: yogurt salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; drain, mash and beat until fluffy.
Add other ingredients; beat until smooth and fluffy.
Can add a little milk if too stiff.
Put in casserole and put in refrigerator. (Casserole can be sprayed with Pam.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: dreamy salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Combine jello and sugar; stir in boiling water.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
(Note: You can use the juice from the canned pineapple as part of the cup of liquid.)
Whip Dream Whip and mix with the cream cheese, almonds and marshmallows; combine with jello mixture.
Add pineapple and turn into dish for chilling until set.

title: garlic and shrimp linguini
directions: Stir-fry broccoli in 1/4 cup of the olive oil in a wok or frying pan for about five minutes.
Add remaining oil, then add mushrooms and stir-fry for five minutes.
Add shrimp, garlic, onion, lemon rind, salt and pepper.
Stir-fry for five minutes. Add buttered linguini to wok.
Sprinkle with Romano.
Toss well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until mixture is thoroughly blended
and
foamy.
Add
remaining ingredients, blending thoroughly	and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Allow to cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sit overnight in refrigerator.
Serve next day.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Fold in dates, lemon juice and vanilla; pour into pastry shell.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: fat man's pie
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups flour, 1 stick margarine (melted) and 1 cup nuts.
Mix well and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and then cool.
Mix 8 ounces cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 (8 or 9 ounce) carton of Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix 2 large packages chocolate instant pudding with 4 cups milk.
When thickened, spread over 2nd layer.
Spread with 8 or 9 ounce carton Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening thoroughly. Add buttermilk and yeast, dissolved in water.
Mix with spoon until all flour is moistened.
Cover bowl and put into refrigerator until ready to use.
When ready to use, take out as much dough as needed.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut biscuits.
Bake at 400° on cookie sheet for 12 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together ingredients, except limeade and orange slices. Stir well, place in large containers and freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer at least 2 hours before ready to serve.
Add limeade and orange slices before serving.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Spoon sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour all soda in bowl.
Stir and pour into cups.
Enjoy.

title: spicy dipping sauce for mushrooms
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Rinse and dry mushrooms. Halve the large mushrooms.
Makes 2 cups of sauce.
Also, good for other raw vegetables.

title: peppermint bark
directions: Melt almond bark on low heat, stirring frequently, to prevent scorching. When melted, add 1 cup well crushed peppermint candy. Stir.
May add a few drops of red food coloring to achieve pink color.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Combine peeled and sliced apples with 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Put into 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Cut in margarine for crumb mixture.
Sprinkle on top of apples and bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: wesley's candy
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Roll dough into small 1-inch balls.
Serve immediately or store in closed container in refrigerator.

title: crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter; slowly add sugar, beaten eggs, vanilla flavoring and slowly add flour.
Chill dough.
Roll on floured board and cut.
Bake until light brown, about 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: chutney cheese ball
directions: Cream together cream cheese and chutney, which has been chopped into small pieces. Add curry powder and when thoroughly mixed, roll into a ball
and put in Saran Wrap; refrigerate. After it is thoroughly chilled, roll in chopped almonds or pecans. Serve with Ginger Snaps. This freezes very well for future use.

title: chunky potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large kettle, saute onion in margarine for 3 minutes.
Add potatoes, water, celery leaves, salt, pepper, paprika and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are just tender, stirring occasionally.

title: baked sausages with peppers
directions: Poke sausages with fork in a few places.
Slice potatoes and onions.
Cut peppers into strips.
In large pan, layer onions, potatoes and peppers.
Place sausages on top of vegetables. Sprinkle with spices.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
During baking time, stir vegetables and sausages around to coat with juices.
You may add half the peppers after 25 minutes of cooking time since they cook quickly. Sprinkle green onions over top before serving.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream drops
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and eggs. Stir in sour cream, vanilla and flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes until almost no imprint remains when lightly touched.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place the chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cover each with a slice of cheese.
Warm the soup and milk together until smooth.
Pour over the chicken and cheese.
Melt the magarine and toss with the stuffing mix.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco oil and eggs; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to Crisco oil mixture and beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Add grated carrots and nuts.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: kari's chicken
directions: Mix all together and roll up in crescent rolls. Bake by directions on crescent rolls.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients real well; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 1/2-inch dish. Refrigerate until firm.

title: turnip puff
directions: Combine turnip and eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well and put in buttered casserole dish.
Mix 1/4 cup dry bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted oleo; sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, celery seed, vinegar, salt and oil together; boil until sugar is dissolved.
Pour hot over cabbage, pepper and onions; mix well.
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and refrigerate.
Will keep a long time.

title: hidden pear salad
directions: In a saucepan, boil pear liquid.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Remove and cool until syrupy.
Puree pears in blender. Beat cream cheese and lemon juice until fluffy and smooth. Prepare whipped topping by directions.
Fold into pear mixture, then into cooled jello.
Pour into oiled mold.
Chill overnight. Unmold on lettuce.

title: baked eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and boil eggplant until done.
Fry onion and garlic until done.
Add crab meat and shrimp.
Drain and mash eggplant and add to other ingredients; mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs and butter, which have been mixed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and water until bubbly and thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
I don't add salt, but you may.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan cook milk, margarine, cocoa, sugar and salt together.
Boil at low heat for 3 minutes.
Remove pan from stove and stir in peanut butter, vanilla and quick oats until well mixed. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: raisin rolls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk, water, eggs and butter. Mix and make dough.
Place dough in covered bowl and let rise for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: confectioners sugar glaze
directions: Stir milk into sugar.
Drizzle on dessert cakes, muffins and cookies.
You can substitute lemon juice for milk for a lemon flavored glaze.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: rainbow s'morsels
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixer bowl, blend flour, cracker crumbs, butter, sugar, brown sugar and salt until crumbly.
Press into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes in orange sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Let come to a boil.
Boil until slightly thickened.
Cut cooked yams and place in oblong casserole.
Slice an orange and place slices on yams.
Pour orange sauce over yams. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add the remaining ingredients and work in flour until you have a soft dough.
Roll out into desired shapes.
Let rise until double and bake in a hot oven or let rise and bake them in a 300° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until just good and firm, not brown. Then store them in freezer for later use.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes great toast.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix flour and margarine together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cream cheese and sugar together and spread over cooled crust.
Refrigerate.
Mix pudding (any flavor) with milk as directed on package.
Spread over cream cheese and top with Cool Whip.
Add chopped nuts for garnish.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with Italian seasoning.
Combine all ingredients and fold into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle 8 to 12 ounces of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted but not brown.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift and mix well flour, soda, salt and spices.
Mix and add oil, buttermilk, sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Add candied fruits (optional).
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: sourdough cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar and butter.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Sift 1 cup flour with soda and salt.
Add to milk, beating with a wooden spoon until mixture is smooth.
Beat in sourdough starter and 1 1/2 cups flour to make a dough easy to handle.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead for about 8 minutes or until smooth.
Put dough in greased or oiled bowl, turning to grease surface lightly.
Cover with towel and let rise in warm place until doubled (it rises very slowly).

title: oatmeal-peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat until blended and drop onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: mother's pear mincemeat
directions: Put all ingredients through food chopper.
Cook until tender. If thick, add more vinegar.
Cook on simmer for 30 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add sugar, salt and egg.
Add mixture to 1 1/2 cups flour and add shortening.
Add the remaining 1 1/2 cups flour and grease the top.
Let rise to double in size and punch down to take out desired amount.
Make into rolls and let rise.
Bake at 400° until ready.
Mixture can be put in refrigerator for up to 4 days.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Mix in nuts and marshmallows.
Roll out on waxed paper.
Let cool; cut.

title: almond cheese cake
directions: Place foil baking liners in 12 muffin pan cups. In a large bowl, mix the cheese until smooth.
Beat in eggs, sugar, milk, flour, lemon peel and extract until well blended.
Spoon into cups.
Arrange almonds on cupcakes.
Bake 30 minutes at 375° or until set.
Cool on wire rack.
Spoon jam into center of each cooled cupcake.

title: kathy's easy biscuit sticks
directions: Melt margarine in a large Pyrex dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk.
Stir with a fork.
Knead on floured wax paper 10 times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in sticks 3/4-inch wide; roll in melted butter.
Bake at 450° until brown (15 minutes).

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix well.
Pour in 2 pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: homemade sandwich buns
directions: Melt butter; saute onion in small saucepan until tender but not browned.
Add yogurt and water; blend well and heat until very warm, nearly 120°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, flour and nutmeg in a Dutch oven; set aside to allow syrup to form, about 15 minutes.
Bring peach mixture to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and margarine.

title: all-italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
In large shallow baking pan, shape into loaf with cheese in center, sealing edges tightly.
Bake 50 minutes or until done.
Top, if desired, with additional spatini spaghetti sauce. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
"Buon appetito."

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Steep tea bags in 8 cups water.
Set aside.
Mix cinnamon sticks and cloves in remaining water; bring to a boil and add sugar.
Bring to a boil again for 3 to 5 minutes.
Strain and mix with tea.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice. Heat to almost boiling (a crock-pot works great; mixture can also be stored in a refrigerator and then heated at serving time.)

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in hot oil. Add garlic and cook until yellow. Add soy sauce, salt and 1/4 cup water. Lower heat and cook for approximately 45 minutes (check to see if more liquid is needed). Add vegetables, except tomatoes, and cook for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Thaw shrimp and chop.
Melt cheese and soup on low heat.
Add pepper, onion and shrimp.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 tablespoons hot water.
Mix and stir.
Let cool.
Add mayonnaise and salt.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Coat biscuits with mixture and layer in Bundt or ring pan.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Optional: Carrots, cauliflower, broccoli, radishes and sprouts.

title: pineapple sour cream dessert
directions: Chill all ingredients except pudding and nutmeg before mixing. Mix together pineapple, dry pudding and milk.
Mix until thick. Fold in sour cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Chill.
Nut meats may also be added.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until thick, about 12 minutes. Add 1 1/3 cup coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Beat until light and spreadable.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Blend together until well blended.
(Add a little milk, if needed.)
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Can be refrigerated ahead and baked later.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Alternately add eggs and flour, blending thoroughly.
Add flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven; let cake cool 15 minutes before removing from oven.

title: spaghetti and hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper, then mushrooms and ripe olives as desired.
In kettle, combine and boil tomatoes, tomato sauce and water, then add spaghetti (long).
As much as you can hold in your hand, break in half.
Add meat mixture and cook until done.

title: grandma's old-fashioned italian cookies
directions: Combine sugar, flour (add flour as needed before and after eggs are added), baking powder and lard.
Work with hands until crumbly.
Then add eggs, flour and vanilla; work again until hand rollable.
Shape cookies into balls, sticks and twist.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients except buns.
Fill buns; wrap in aluminum foil.
Place in slow oven (250°) about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand for 1 hour, covered with plastic wrap. Cream together butter and sugars. Add flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda to sugar mixture. Mix well; blend in egg-raisin mixture and oatmeal. Dough will be stiff. Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet or roll into small balls and flatten slightly on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well mixed. Bake in layers at 350° approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken
directions: In Corning Ware, place your favorite pieces of chicken.
Cover with sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook in 300° oven (covered) until tender.

title: mozzarella frys
directions: Combine egg yolks and sugar.
Beat at high speed until mixture is thick and piles softly.
Add cheese and salt, then mix in flour, one tablespoon at a time.
Add just enough flour to form a dough.
(Dough will be sticky.)

title: mar's mexican chicken breasts
directions: Put a layer of chips on bottom of a large casserole or baking dish. Spread chopped chicken over chips.
Heat broth, soup, chiles, onion and mushrooms.
Remove from heat. Add sour cream and pour over chicken. Sprinkle grated cheese over top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Line edge of casserole with remaining corn chips.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add fruit cocktail, egg and oleo and mix.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar or cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch in a pan.
Bring to boil stirring constantly until clear.
Remove from heat.
Add Jello. Spread a little on bottom of pie shell.
Add strawberries.
Pour Jello mixture on top.
Chill.

title: molded cranberry cabbage salad
directions: *Use red cabbage for more flavor.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 5 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Stuff jalapenos with grated cheese and boiled shrimp.
Wrap with a strip of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Grill on charcoal grill with peppers wrapped in foil; punch holes in the foil.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Spread in heatproof dish.
Spread with heated meat chili.
Place shredded Cheddar over chili.
Garnish with finely chopped green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Dump vegetables into pot.
Add water.
Sprinkle dry mix over top.
Stir	to
blend.
Cook until vegetables are tender. One-half cup equals 1 vegetable exchange.

title: skillet chili
directions: In large skillet, heat oil.
Add onion and garlic; saute 3 or 4 minutes.
Add hamburger; cook until meat is thoroughly cooked. Now add broth, paste and mustard.
Blend and bring to a boil. Lower heat; cook 8 minutes, partially covered, stirring occasionally.
Toss with macaroni and parsley.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese balls
directions: Beat well with mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese and blend.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Shape cheese into 2 balls.
Roll into nuts. Refrigerate.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain. Put in casserole dish top with soup, cheese and tater tots. Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato gnocchi
directions: Scrub potatoes; cook
in jackets in boiling water until tender.
Peel, press
through ricer and measure (packed lightly). For 4 cups of
potatoes, add 2 cups flour.	Add eggs and salt; mix well.
Divide
mixture
into
small
portions.
Roll each portion with palms of hands on lightly floured board to a rope 1 inch thick.
Cut
into
half inch slices.
With floured finger press indentation in
side
of
each.
This
little cup will hold sauce when serving.
Drop
gnocchi, a few at a time, into
boiling salted water.
When
gnocchi
rise	to
surface remove from water with
slotted spoon.
Serve with your favorite tomato sauce. Serves about 8.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil, stirring constantly; add onion, celery and hamburger and continue browning.
Drain all grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until the rice is tender.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind onions, tomatoes and green peppers.
In a large bowl combine ground vegetables, beans, cauliflower and corn.
Sprinkle pickling salt.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.

title: blt dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: tomato welsh rarebit
directions: Melt cheese in pan over hot water.
Heat soup with all remaining ingredients except egg.
Add soup mixture to cheese. Add egg and mix thoroughly over hot water for 5 minutes.
Serve on toast or crackers.
Keeps for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: yummy pork chops
directions: Dredge chops in mixture of flour,salt,dry mustard and garlic powder. Brown in oil in large skillet. Place browned chops in crok-pot and add soup. Cover and cook 6-8 hr. low setting, then high for 3 1/2 hr.

title: dakota dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
In a large casserole, mix together with beans, tomatoes and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Potatoes can be precooked to speed up baking.)

title: aloha mocha sweet treat
directions: In blender, combine cold coffee, milk, ice cream, fudge sauce and peanut butter.
Blend 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour in tall glasses.
Sprinkle cocoa on top.

title: four cheese vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles, omitting salt and fat. Drain; set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together and put in greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: savory one-dish meal
directions: Place butter, green pepper, onion and beef into a 2-quart casserole dish and brown over medium heat.
Add the peas and mushrooms or substitute tomato sauce for the mushrooms.

title: candy corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, but popped corn, in saucepan.
Cook to 250°.
Pour over popcorn.
Shape into balls or break into bite-size pieces.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in skins and peel.
Place in bottom of dish. Cover with preceding mixture.
Let stand 24 hours before serving. Can be refrigerated for two weeks.

title: orange-cantaloupe drink(low-fat, low cholesterol, low calorie, high fiber, low sodium)
directions: Extract juice from orange (1/2 cup), cantaloupe (1/2 cup) and lemon (1 tablespoon), using juice extractor.
Pour fruit juices over ice.
Stir before serving.
Makes 1 serving.

title: zesty vegie soup
directions: In large pot brown small meatballs with onion.
Cook until onion is tender; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegies are tender.

title: microwave liver and onions
directions: Coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Place bacon and onion in a 2-quart casserole.
Cook in microwave, covered, on Full power for 8 to 10 minutes or until bacon is almost crisp.
Remove bacon and onions.
Add liver to bacon fat.
Cook on Full power for 5 to 7 minutes or until liver is no longer pink.
Turn liver over halfway through cooking time.
Put onions and bacon on top of liver.
Cook on Full power for 1 minute or until heated through.

title: punch
directions: Mix Hawaiian Punch, limeade and strawberries.
A few minutes before serving, add ice and ginger ale.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Beat 3 eggs.
Add milk mixture.
Add bread and broccoli with pinch of salt.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: cucumber snack
directions: Mix and pour over sliced cucumbers.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine and add flour and salt.
Stir in vanilla and almond flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool on a rack.

title: lemon chicken(texas-style)
directions: Also good with onions, mushrooms and white wine.

title: funny, funny faces
directions: Scoop ice cream into cone.
Using M&M's, create facial features.
Sprinkle candy sprinkles on top of ice cream.
Use whatever toppings desired.

title: mozzarella loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut Italian bread crosswise into 1-inch slices, being careful not to cut through bottom crust.
Cut Mozzarella cheese into 1/4-inch thick slices and place slices between bread slices.
Place bread on cookie sheet and bake for about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and bread is heated through.
Sprinkle loaf with oregano.
With a sharp knife, divide loaf into slices by cutting through the bottom crust.
Serve immediately.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Ready when it turns loose from the sides. Knead and store in an airtight container.

title: scalloped asparagus and artichokes
directions: Cut asparagus in half lengthwise.
Place asparagus, artichokes and mushrooms into layers in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter and blend in flour.
Slowly add milk and artichoke juice, stirring to make a thick cream sauce.
Add salt, pepper and half of grated cheese to the sauce.
Pour over the vegetables.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: california sushi
directions: Bring to a boil and cool the vinegar, sugar, salt and ajinomoto.
Mix into rice.
Cut 20 sheets of yaki (roasted) nori in half.
Cut vegetables into 1/4 x 2-inch strips.
Arrange vegetables on a platter with a small dish of prepared horseradish to sparingly spread over rice as people roll their own sushi.
To make a sushi, a person would take a nori sheet, place a thin layer of sushi rice over the nori; place some horseradish over rice and place any combination of vegetables in the center.
Roll nori into a cone shape or into a jellyroll shape before eating.

title: enchilada dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Blend kidney beans and juice in blender.
Mix beans with browned beef and onion.
Add chili powder, ketchup, salt and mustard.
Top with Colby shredded cheese, sliced black olives and chopped onions.

title: beans and sausage
directions: Cook sausage and onion for about 15 to 20 minutes; do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until bean soup turns brown, about 15 minutes.
Cook rice and add to the cooked beans mixture.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat peanut butter, water, eggs and 1/2 cup dry cake mix.
Mix until blended and smooth.
Add remaining cake mix and mix well.
Dry dough by placing 1 teaspoon 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: party rye treats
directions: Mix crumbled raw bacon, cheese, onion, celery seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in a plastic container; store overnight.
Before using, set out overnight to soften.
Mix again and spread on slices of party rye.
Place under broiler and brown. Delicious!

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain the pineapple and reserve the juice.
Mix egg, sugar and flour and add to the pineapple juice.
Cook slowly until the mixture thickens.
Combine the pineapple chunks, marshmallows and the cheese.
Pour the cooked mixture over the pineapple combination in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until slightly brown.
A great dish for a vegetable meal!

title: out of this world salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add cream cheese and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add pineapple, sugar, vanilla and pecans. Stir.
Add 7-Up; stir well and chill until set.
When it begins to jell, pour into a mold or oblong dish.

title: forty-niners
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine everything, mixing well. Spread out on cookie sheet (with sides) or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, cut into squares.

title: nell's quick coffee cake
directions: Mix flour and shortening. Beat egg, sugar, and milk together, then stir all together and pour in greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2. Sprinkle topping mixture over batter and bake in 375° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken salad log
directions: Mix thoroughly cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, ginger, red pepper sauce, chicken and green onions.
Form into shape of loaf on serving platter.
Divide into 4 sections by laying 3 strips of thinly sliced bell pepper across loaf.
Press 4 different garnishes (sesame seed, black olives, pimentos, etc.) into each of the 4 sections created.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
May be served with many different kinds of crackers placed on the serving dish.

title: lime chiffon salad
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter; stir in crumbs.
Pat firmly on bottom of an 8-inch square pan or 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish. Chill.
In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in sweetened milk, pineapple and ReaLime.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Put in pan and chill 2 hours or until set. Garnish with lime twists if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers. Serves 12.

title: hominy casserole
directions: In a saucepan, mix and heat oleo, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over hominy and onions.
Mix; put in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown.
Top with crushed fritos.

title: ginger pumpkin frost
directions: Combine first 5 or six ingredients.
Soften ice cream and fold into pumpkin mixture.
Place a layer of gingersnap crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour in ice cream mixture; sprinkle with a layer of gingersnap crumbs.
Freeze until very firm.
Remove from freezer 15 to 30 minutes before serving.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package instructions.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.
Great for a covered dish.

title: 8 minute light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir 3 minutes.
Add ice; stir until jello thickens (2-3 minutes).
Remove ice cubes.
Blend in Cool Whip with wire whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill mixture until it will mound.
Spoon into graham crust.
Chill 3 hours.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Arrange washed scallops in a 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Pour 1/2 of half and half over scallops.
Mix bread crumb, oleo, salt and pepper and sprinkle over scallops.
Top with remaining half and half.
Cook uncovered in 375° oven until hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate angel cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add beaten egg whites.
Melt chocolate bits and add to egg mixture.
Whip cream with 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Fold into chocolate/egg mixture.
Tear cake into bite sized pieces.
Place 1/2 of cake and 1/2 of sauce in 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan, then, rest of cake and rest of sauce.
Chill 3 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fruit crumble
directions: Place fruit in greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over fruit and bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Prepare chicken for cooking (use pressure pot, put enough water to cover chicken parts, about 6 cups.
Salt and pepper. Cook for 15 minutes.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat.
Stir in pecans until well coated.
Bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 30 minutes; stir while baking.
Drain on paper towels and salt while still warm.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Divide into 4 rolls.
Bake at 225° for 4 hours on a rack in flat pans.
Dry with paper towels.
Store, wrapped in foil.

title: chocolate gravy(good on cake and ice cream)
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Have water boiling in saucepan.
Add cocoa and sugar mixture; salt.
Gradually stir in flour mixture. Remove from burner and stir in vanilla.
Serve hot or cold.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Grease a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour, add milk slowly and stir constantly.
Cook over low heat until comes to a boil.
Add drained salmon, flake into pieces. Remove bones.
Add celery, onions, salt, pepper and dry mustard. Beat egg yolks and add to salmon.
Beat egg whites until they hold peak.
Fold into salmon mixture very gently.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(I serve this with the mixed vegetable casserole.)

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine in saucepan sugar and cornstarch; mix well to avoid lumps.
Add egg yolks to milk.
Cook slowly until thickened.
Add butter and vanilla.
After butter has completely melted, add coconut; stir.
Pour into precooked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.

title: buttered glazed turnips
directions: Cook turnips until tender in boiling water in which bouillon cube is dissolved.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Drizzle with melted margarine or butter; sprinkle with sugar and pepper as desired.
Additional salt may not be needed when bouillon is used. Place in 350° oven for about 15 minutes until flavors are blended.
Serve hot.

title: dilly macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain well. Cool.
Combine macaroni, cheese, celery, green pepper and pimento.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Soften ice cream slightly and let lemonade thaw before mixing. Mix ice cream and lemonade together with a mixer.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with Cool Whip topping.
Freeze.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoning salt. Wrap each breast with bacon. Butter pan and line with beef.
Arrange breasts over beef. Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over breasts.
Chill several hours. Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: simply sinful
directions: Generously butter a loaf or jelly roll pan.
Line bottom with graham crackers.
Melt 1/2 pound butter.
Add sugar and cook over low heat until bubbly.
Pour butter-sugar mixture over crackers. Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes at 350°. Watch closely.
Butter should be browned, but not burned.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugars, oil, butter and eggs until fluffy.
Stir in sifted flour, soda, cream of tartar, salt and flavoring.
Beat until well blended.
Place on waxed paper and chill 3 hours.
Roll in small balls and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until light brown.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: cottage cheese muffins
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and cottage cheese.
Add lemon peel, egg, Bisquick and milk.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: easy english pea casserole
directions: Heat peas until tender; drain.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Heat over low flame until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and half of fried onions.
Pour mixture into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with remaining fried onions.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: blitz kuchen(cinnamon crisps)
directions: Mix
all ingredients.
Spread dough as thinly as possible on a
12 x 16-inch greased cookie sheet.
Brush with milk and cover with
cinnamon
mixture
of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon to taste.
Dot with small pieces of butter.
Bake at 350° on
lowest rack
until
crisp, about 15 minutes.
Cut in diagonal pieces while hot.

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: Spray Bundt pan.
Place rolls in pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Mix melted butter, sugar and cinnamon together; pour over rolls.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cover with cloth overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked onions(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat honey, margarine or butter and salt in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Arrange onions in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes until fork-tender and golden brown.

title: blender casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put all ingredients in blender.
Process on chop approximately 12 seconds or until all are chopped.
Pour into casserole.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered.

title: potato rolls
directions: Heat milk, potatoes and oleo until very warm.
Put in large container (Tupperware Fix-N-Mix size) and add sugar, salt, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Mix well and let stand for 2 hours.
(It will be like a sponge.)

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix water and jello.
Add bananas, pineapple and strawberries. Divide mixture.
Chill 1/2 in flat container.
Leave 1/2 unchilled.
Spread sour cream over chilled mixture.
Pour remainder over sour cream and chill.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix as other biscuits; roll out on pastry sheet.
Cut, put in pans and let rise one hour.
Bake 12 minutes at 425°.

title: chicken cheese puffs
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; beat until smooth.
Add milk and beat.
Stir in chicken and pepper.
Unroll dough and separate into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup of mixture into each rectangle.
Moisten edges of rectangle with water.
Bring corners to center over filling.
Pinch edges to seal. Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Bring everything to room temperature.

title: taco rice
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients, draining tomatoes before adding.
Add enough water to juice to
make
2 1/2 cups
liquid.
Simmer until liquid is gone and
rice
is tender. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top until melted.

title: ruth's corn pudding
directions: Allow corn to thaw before cooking.
Combine all ingredients and cook in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan with Crisco and flour.
Mix cake mix with pudding, 4 eggs and 7-Up.
Mix on high speed for about 5 minutes.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mother phoebe seller's easy potato au gratin
directions: Slice potatoes.
Layer bottom of casserole dish with potatoes. Place 1 teaspoon of margarine, divided in 4 sections, on top of potatoes.
Place a layer of mushroom soup.
Repeat two times until there are 3 layers. Bake in a covered casserole dish in medium oven at 325° to 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fantasy fudge
directions: In a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.

title: forgotten roast
directions: Wipe roast and place on foil.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Pour cream of celery soup over roast.
Wrap very tightly in foil. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roast at 275° for 4 hours and forget it.
Roast makes its own gravy.

title: cornstarch pudding
directions: Pour about 2 cups milk in blender; add cornstarch, sugar, vanilla and egg yolks and blend.
Meanwhile, heat rest of milk in large pan; when hot, pour in cornstarch mixture and stir over medium-high heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Put ladyfingers in large bowl.
Pour pudding over them.
Beat egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar until thick, then drop by spoon on top of pudding.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400° or until lightly brown.

title: hot bean dip(crock-pot)
directions: Pour all ingredients in order listed into crock-pot.
Cook on high 45 minutes or until cheese melts.
Turn heat to low.
Cook 3 hours or until party starts!
Serve with tortilla chips. Leftovers may be frozen.

title: nutrasweet chocolate pie(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients except Equal.
Cook on High 2 minutes; stir.
Cook on High 2 minutes; stir.
Cook and stir every 1 minute until thick.
Add small amount of chocolate to egg yolks, then return to chocolate mix.
Cook on Medium (1/2 power) for 1 minute. Cook on Medium 1 minute; stir.
Add margarine; stir.
Pour into baked pie crust.
After pie cools some, put in Equal (heat takes some sweetness away).
Add meringue.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit well.
Pour melted oleo over fruit in a buttered casserole.
Mix together brown sugar, cornstarch and curry powder. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, shortening and salt.
Beat with electric mixer until shortening is melted.
Add eggs and beat well.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Mix in flour one cup at a time.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Use all of dough or amount wanted.
Dough will keep in refrigerator 10 days.
Knead well; roll out and cut into biscuits.
Let stand in warm place at least 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 24 rolls.

title: d's date delight
directions: Bring to boil the dates, water and salt; simmer for 3 minutes and add marshmallows.
Cool.
Add chopped pecans.

title: sausage and italian vegetables
directions: Cook, drain and crumble sausage.
In skillet, combine sausage, vegetables, tomato sauce and garlic to taste.
Simmer while preparing rice according to directions.
Serve sausage and vegetable combo over rice.

title: hamburger and potato bake
directions: Cook hamburger and onions; drain off fat.
Boil potatoes until almost tender.
Drain.
Put potatoes in casserole dish; add hamburger and onions.
Put celery soup over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.
Ten minutes before done, top with cheese; cook 10 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds and wash peppers.
Cook peppers 5 minutes; drain. Cook hamburger, onion and mushrooms.
Drain.
Stir in salt, garlic salt, rice and tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
Stuff peppers; pour remaining sauce over peppers.
Cover; cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover; cook 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Fillet bass with scales left on.
Wash, clean and marinate in Italian dressing.
Place on aluminum foil and grill until done.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together well.
Using a level tablespoon for each, form into a ball.
Roll in powdered sugar. Store in an airtight tin or cracker container.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: cherry cheesecake delight
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add cherry pie filling.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cherry mixture.
Sprinkle a few graham cracker crumbs over all.
Chill.

title: lemon wafers(about 5 dozen)
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, lemon and vanilla extract.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add, a little at a time, along with milk, mixing well.
Chill for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: creamy seafood dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, salad dressing and lemon juice. Add salad mix, onion and celery. Mix well. Serve with crackers. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions on box.
Add Cool Whip, butter and vanilla flavoring after mixing well.
Layer in pan.
Start with cookies on bottom to make a good crust.
Then pour all pudding mixture next.
Sprinkle the rest of the cookies on top of pudding.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: aunt millie's fondant(from the files of viola clark williams)
directions: Cook to hard boil stage (10 to 15 minutes).
While cooking whip continually by hand 2 egg whites.
When hard boil stage is reached, add to whites slowly; whip until firm.
Add nuts and vanilla, then work fast with a teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Baking time varies according to size of cake pan used.
Place egg whites in a deep bowl and beat until stiff but not dry.
In a large bowl beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Slowly add sifted sugar and mix thoroughly.
In a separate bowl, sift flour and sift it again with baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites and mix again.
Scald butter with milk and add slowly to mixture, beating well after each addition until all ingredients are mixed together.

title: party mushroom spread
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in oil in skillet over medium-high heat until excess liquid has evaporated and mushrooms are starting to brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and mustard; heat, but do not boil.
Serve as a spread on Melba rounds or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel
potatoes; cut into quarters.
Beat the eggs until mixed together.
In
a
separate bowl, combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip
potato
in egg, then in flour mixture. Melt butter in
x 9-inch pan.
Place potatoes in a single layer.
Bake
for
about 1 hour, turning once during baking.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add dry butterscotch pudding.
Mix well.
Add oats.
Let cool 15 minutes, then drop onto waxed paper by teaspoon.

title: sugar cookies or press out cookies
directions: Mix sugar and margarine together; pour in milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine all ingredients. Roll large amount onto floured area.
Mixture will be thin but will thicken as flour is added to roll out area.
Now press out your shapes.
Continue until dough is gone.
Put on cookie sheets and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until very light brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix with stuffing.
Place half in pan.
Place chicken on top of this mixture.
Mix soups and broth together; pour on top of chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Boil noodles in 4 to 6 quarts water.
Cook 14 to 16 minutes. Drain and rinse with hot water.

title: grandpa's irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine eggs, margarine and buttermilk.
Stir in raisins.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture, mixing until moist.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch tube pan or 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes for tube pan or 45 minutes for loaf pans.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; continue cooling on wire rack.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar in bottom of Bundt pan.
Pour milk over the sugar.
Stand biscuits in bottom of pan on their edges.
Pour mixture of melted oleo and 1 cup brown sugar over biscuits.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for a few minutes, then flip onto plate.
Serve warm.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Combine together soups and remaining ingredients.
Mash Doritos up and mix well.
Bake in oven for 25 minutes.
Remove and add grated cheese on top.
Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add to milk and bring mixture to a boil.

title: 100 sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, margarine, oil, eggs, vanilla, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add flour, one cup at a time, beating after adding each cup.
Roll dough into small balls or drop by teaspoon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down each cookie ball with the bottom of a glass, dipping glass in melted margarine and then in sugar.
Bake at 350°, about 10 minutes or until light golden brown on edge.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Steam vegetables.
Cool and toss with spices.
Place pita bread on cookie sheet.
Portion seasoned vegetables onto breads. Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese melts and becomes slightly browned.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts, then coconut in pan. Cream the cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Set aside. Mix cake to package directions and pour on top of nuts and coconut. Drop cream cheese on top of cake.
Do not spread to edge.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana bran bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add all-bran; mix well. Break 1 egg right into mixture.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add this mixture alternately to first mixture with bananas, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Let stand in loaf pan 1/2 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: davy crockett bars
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix. Stir in vanilla, nuts and chocolate bits.
Put in shallow layers on cake pans.
Make glaze from 10x sugar and milk.
Put this on bars when removing from oven.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars.
Makes 48 (2 1/2-inch) bars.
Do not overbake!

title: coconut ball
directions: Brown coconut and pecans in broiler of oven. Combine brown sugar, evaporated milk and butter in saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil and boil 2 to 3 minutes until it becomes thick syrup.
Put saucepan in pan of hot water.
Place marshmallows on long fork. Dip in brown sugar-milk mixture, making sure marshmallow is coated.
Roll in coconut-pecan mixture
and shape into a ball.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt oleo and saute vegetables until wilted.
Add crawfish tails and cook 10 minutes.
Add the soup, water and wine.
Stir and simmer with lid on for about 20 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and green onions; simmer 5 or 10 minutes more.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: ham casserole
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water, drain and rinse with cold water.
Cool.

title: country carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, oil, soda and spices well.
Fold in carrots, nuts, coconut and pineapple. Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fancy biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine ingredients as you would for regular biscuits.
Store dough in tightly closed plastic bag or bowl in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Do not let rise at any time.
Roll out and bake on a greased pan in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix water, sugar, pineapple juice and orange juice.
Put lemon juice and bananas in blender; blend until smooth.
Add banana mixture and ginger ale just before serving.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli medley
directions: Mix all together and bake in a moderate oven
(350°) until hot through and bubbly in the center.

title: two rivers woman's club raspberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, frozen raspberries and juice, oil and dry Jell-O mix together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: angel rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, add oil and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well (you don't need a mixer).
Store covered in refrigerator overnight.
Pinch off as much as needed, add enough self-rising flour to make a soft dough.
Knead by hand a few minutes.
Shape into rolls or cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Batter will keep a week, use as needed.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Blend above ingredients and last of all add 1 cup boiling water. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash berries; grind in blender.
(You may need to add a small amount of water to help this process.)
Drain in a colander.
Pour sugar over berries; refrigerate overnight in a covered container. Add the drained pineapple, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in the whipped cream and chill.
May be refrigerated, covered, for several days.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, then drain off fat and add onion and green pepper. Brown, then add other ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: better than potato salad
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, cucumber, celery, onion, radishes, and chopped eggs.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix well.
Pour over rice mixture and toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. (Serves 12.)

title: los siete magnificos
directions: Serve with Fritos chips.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream shortening and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add salt, baking powder, flour and milk.
Mix well.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Prepare oranges.
Heat peach juice and pour over gelatin to dissolve.
Add all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm (serves 12).

title: corn fritters
directions: Preheat oil to 350°.

title: holiday cake
directions: Sift flour with
baking
powder
and
salt.
Cream 1 cup butter and 2
cups sugar.
Add dry ingredients with milk.
Beat egg whites until
stiff.
Fold
into cake mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in layers at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ratatouille(the word means stew or soup in french.)
directions: Dice eggplant into 1-inch cubes and slice zucchini in 1/2-inch rounds.
Chop onion coarsely and cut green pepper into squares. Use a heavy bottomed saucepan with lid and saute onion, garlic and green pepper until soft.
Stir in eggplant and zucchini; saute a few minutes more.
Crush garlic with a fork.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer gently for about 30 minutes or until the vegetables are well cooked.

title: oil and garlic sauce for pasta
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil until golden brown.
Add water, parsley and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked pasta; add 1/4 to 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Toss well.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Roll or shape into balls. Then roll in pecans.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat until smooth. Pare and slice 5 medium apples or 1 (20 ounce) can of "pie sliced apples", drained. Grease tube pan. Pour 1/2 of the batter into pan and top with apples. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Pour remaining batter over apple slices and top with remaining half of the apples. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. (Two layers of apples, one in the middle and one on top.) Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let cool for 10 minutes in pan and turn out on cake plate. Do not ice. Freezes well.
