title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat chicken breasts with flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in 5 tablespoons of butter and remove.
Arrange breasts close together in shallow pan.
Add onions to pan drippings; cook until tender.
Stir in chicken broth and wine; bring to boil and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour or more, until chicken is tender.
Cook mushrooms in remaining 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add to chicken, along with grapes.
Cover and continue to bake for 10 minutes.

title: curried beef and rice
directions: Cook onion in margarine, stirring frequently, until tender. Stir in beef, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until beef is hot.
Stir into hot rice.
Sprinkle with almonds and olives.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas corn chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with tortilla chips.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs; beat well. Sift dry ingredients together. Add coconut extract to milk. Add dry and wet ingredients to sugar mixture, ending with dry. Fold in flaked coconut. Bake in a large tube or Bundt pan which has been greased and floured. Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack or cake stand to finish cooling.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine at medium speed until combined. Gradually add egg substitute, beating well.
Combine sour cream and baking soda; stir well and set aside.
Combine flour and salt; at low speed, add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into 10-inch tube pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: lazy day beef stew
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 2 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of first 5 ingredients. Place half the potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole; cover with half the onion and half the sauce. Repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour. Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: black fruit cake
directions: Cream the fat until it is very light.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Beat the eggs very light and add to the sugar mixture.
Add cream, juice and molasses.
Mix the flour, soda, spices, fruit, rind and nuts together and add to the first mixture. Line pans with waxed paper and pack mixture in 2/3 full.
Let stand 24 hours before baking.
Bake at 250° until cake springs back to the touch (about 1 1/2 hours for a 5-pound cake is usually correct).
Half of the recipe makes 2 good sized cakes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Cool, debone and cut chicken in bite sized pieces.
Cook vegetables. Drain and set aside.
Cook butter, onion and celery in skillet until tender.
Add soup and broth.
Add spices to taste.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: date logs
directions: Mix butter, sugar, dates and eggs.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes. Cool.
Add nuts and Rice Krispies.
Shape into logs.
Roll in coconut.

title: jello "poke" pie
directions: Bake cake according to directions in oblong pan.
Let cool and poke holes in cake with a fork.
Mix jello with 1 cup hot water and pour over cake.
Refrigerate cake for 2 hours.
Frost with Cool Whip before serving.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, continuing to stir.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into greased Pyrex dish and chill.
Cut into squares with warm knife.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: For biscuit topping, in medium mixing bowl, stir together the flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and salt.
Using a pastry blender, cut in 2 tablespoons margarine and mix until resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in center, then set the dry mixture aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except nuts.
Shape into a ball. Put chopped nuts all over ball.
Chill. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: shannon's  easy chicken-noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Place in large bowl.
Saute onion in butter and add to noodles.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
(Reserve second 1/2 cup of cheese and sauteed vegetables.) Pour in large Pyrex dish and top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese and vegetables, if desired.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set for 30 minutes to thicken before serving.

title: mom's cranberry bread
directions: Grease & flour a 9x5x3 loaf pan.
Mix all of the ingredients together by hand or with mixer.
Put dough in pan, let it rise for at least 30 minutes.
Bake in oven at 350 for 1 hour.
To test if loaf is done, stick a toothpick in and if it comes out clean, it's ready. This recipe makes one loaf.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cream potatoes with hot milk; add rest of ingredients and put in a 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Chop 3 strips bacon and place in skillet.
Chop onion and brown with bacon.
Add brown sugar, catsup and green beans. Place in baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover part of the time.

title: healthy eggs
directions: In a bowl combine all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie crust.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes; lower heat to 325° and bake for 20 minutes or until set.

title: red rice
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in butter.
Add mixture to rice.
Mix well.
Add sausage, sugar, ketchup and water to rice and mix well.
Pour mixture into 3-quart casserole; cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marinade for beef kabobs
directions: Combine all ingredients in large glass jar.
Add cubes of beef or pork.
Marinate for 1 or 2 days.
Shake or turn meat a few times.
Place meat cubes on skewers and cook on grill or under broiler.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Drain well.
Season with salt. In a 10 x 15-inch pan, spread refried beans; cover with prepared meat and chilies.
Cover evenly with shredded cheese, drizzle taco sauce over mixture.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 or 25 minutes.
Garnish with ripe olives, sour cream, avocado dip or all three.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions and chill until syrupy. Grind the apple, orange and cranberries.
Add all ingredients to the chilled Jell-O, then chill until the Jell-O is set.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add flour to melted butter.
Add baking powder and sugar to beaten eggs.
Combine all ingredients and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat oil for frying.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick; cut with donut cutter.
Fry in oil until brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cinnamon rolls or schnecken
directions: Scald the milk and when lukewarm, add sugar, salt and yeast cake.
Let stand 5 minutes and add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat well. Cover and let rise until light.
Add eggs (well beaten), butter and only enough more flour to knead.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.
Invert the spider and remove rolls.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and make into balls.
Put on cookie sheet and chill 3 hours.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Mix and press first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour on top of cake mix mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into 40 squares.

title: woodrow wilson goulash
directions: Brown ground meat until pink color is cooked away. Drain and add onion, chili powder, salt and pepper. Brown 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Add tomatoes, pinto beans and macaroni.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until liquid is cooked down.
Serve with cheese sprinkled on top and with corn chips on side.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased baking dish and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water.
Mix gelatin with 1 cup cold water.
Mix these together and place in refrigerator until it begins to thicken. Add all other ingredients and keep in refrigerator until firm. Cut in squares to serve.

title: deluxe apple pie
directions: Cook until thick.
When cool it should be the consistency of melted caramels.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add ginger ale, marshmallows, pineapple and bananas.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until congealed.
Mix together in a saucepan the powdered sugar, flour, oleo, egg and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool and beat. While cooling, beat in Cool Whip.
Spread over salad.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Mix everything but chicken into a large bowl, then place chicken in a bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate for a least three hours (the longer the better).
Mix around chicken every so often.
Bake in a 400° oven until chicken is lightly crispy.

title: pasta salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Prepare pasta per package directions and drain.
While pasta is cooking, combine and mix all sauce ingredients in a large serving bowl.
Add salt and pepper to taste. While pasta is hot, toss with sauce and serve hot or cold.

title: mixed up snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store leftovers in an airtight container.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Season to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Drop spoonfuls of dough into sugar and roll into balls.
Place balls 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: strawberry-spinach salad
directions: Arrange strawberries in a bowl.
Place next 6 ingredients in blender and with blender running, add oil and vinegar slowly until thoroughly mixed and thickened.
Pour over salad just before serving.

title: hot crab meat appetizer
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, crab meat, onion, milk, horseradish and seasonings.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon into a 9-inch pie plate or ovenproof dish. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 15 minutes.
Serve as dip or spread, with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: walnut romaine salad
directions: In a screw top jar, combine oil, honey, vinegar, wine and ginger.
Cover, shake and chill.
Combine and toss remaining ingredients.
Add walnuts and dressing.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in margarine. Add ground beef; brown.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Place half of spaghetti in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with half of vegetable mix.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Repeat. Mix soup and water until smooth.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: noodles with buttered crumbs
directions: Bring water, salt and oil to a full rolling boil over high heat.
Put in noodles; return to a boil, covering tightly.
Remove from heat; allow to stand for 25 minutes, or until tender, then drain.
Add 1/3 cup butter to noodle pan and melt over low heat. Return noodles to the pan and toss lightly.

title: my friend's spritz
directions: Cream the shortening, margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually blend dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Transfer dough to cookie press and press onto ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until crisp but not brown.

title: buttermilk glaze
directions: Put in a medium saucepan over medium heat, stirring until it comes to a boil.
Poke holes in your favorite carrot cake and pour this glaze over hot cake while glaze is still hot.
Refrigerate.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for 30 minutes.
Add the red kidney beans at this time.

title: chewy snickerdoodles
directions: In a separate bowl combine 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix the butter, applesauce, 1 1/2 cup sugar and the eggs in thoroughly.
Blend in the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Take about a heaping tablespoonful of dough and roll it in cinnamon and sugar in a separate bowl.
Batter will be sticky.
You may need more cinnamon and sugar.
Place on a silver cookie sheet.
Bake for 9 minutes. Cookies will spread big, thin and chewy.

title: spinach picante
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Reserve liquid.
Melt butter and add flour, cooking until smooth but not brown.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Slowly add spinach liquid and milk.
Cook until smooth.
Add seasonings and cheese, stirring until cheese melts. Add spinach and stir.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish; top with stuffing crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potatoes and apple supreme
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon. Combine with potatoes, apples and marshmallows.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter and cover tightly with foil.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 325° or until done.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with marshmallows.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook together bacon, onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued sage spareribs
directions: Place ribs in oven; cover with water.
Add all ingredients except hot pepper and barbecue sauce.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and rinse ribs. Pour hot pepper sauce and barbecue sauce in a large resealable bag; add ribs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Warm ribs to room temperature; drain and reserve marinade.
Grill ribs, uncovered, over medium heat, turning several times until browned.
In saucepan, bring marinade to a boil; stir constantly.
Brush over ribs.

title: wassail
directions: Mix together juices. Bring to a boil covered.
Uncover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake cake.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 1/4 cups hot water.
When partially set add lemon pie filling and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with cake which has been broken into small pieces. Pour jello mixture over cake pieces.
Top with rest of cake pieces and pat down gently.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix well. Stuff peppers and place in greased casserole. Mix 1 cup catsup and 1/2 cup water and pour over top of peppers. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease muffin tins.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pistachio pie(serves 12)
directions: Crush crackers; combine with melted margarine.
Press into 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and cool.

title: hamburger stroganoff casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Combine diluted soup with sour cream; stir into meat mixture.
Add parsley and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine with drained Curly-roni in casserole.
Cover and heat in 250° oven for 15 minutes.

title: stewed chicken french style
directions: Cut chicken in 4 pieces.
Boil carrots and onions for 5 minutes, then drain.
Put the butter in a saucepan with the carrots, onions, parsley and the chicken seasoned with salt.
Heat for a few minutes until the meat becomes firm, but not brown.
Then add the cream and let boil gently for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove the chicken to the serving dish.
Finish by adding a little more cream or if the sauce is not thick enough, add 1 tablespoon of cream sauce or cognac.
Pour over the chicken.
Serves 2.

title: chicken with artichokes and mushrooms
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and fry in butter until browned.
Add mushrooms, wine and sour cream to the chicken and mix well, add artichokes.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender (about 25 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
Serve over egg noodles.
Recipe can be easily doubled.

title: "prosforo" - altar bread
directions: Note:
This bread has no shortening or sugar in it!

title: egg nog pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with eggnog according to package directions for pie filling.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: three-cheese manicotti
directions: Blend tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and 1 1/2 cups water. Simmer uncovered 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine 1 cup of the Mozzarella, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Add eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly.

title: spiced apple pork roast
directions: Remove and discard all excess fat from roast.
Cut slits in top of roast and insert garlic strips.
Mix flour, salt, sugar, mustard and pepper.
Rub over the roast.
Place meat fat side up on a rack in a roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes per pound or until internal temperature reaches 160° to 170°.
Combine applesauce, brown sugar, vinegar and cloves.
Generously brush over roast during last half hour of baking.

title: strawberry velvets
directions: Take cream cheese; mix well in the orange juice.
Put jello in 1 cup hot water; drain the frozen strawberries and use juice in jello.
Stir jello into mayonnaise until chilled and slightly thickened. Fold in the rest of the strawberries.
Pour into 1-quart mold; chill until firm.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Place sweet potato pulp, brown sugar and butter in bowl. Mash with a potato masher.
In another bowl add cottage cheese to beaten egg.
Fold this mixture into the sweet potato mixture.
Put into buttered casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add peanuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise, onion and 2 eggs.
Pour over broccoli, then sprinkle stuffing mix over the top.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: company hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in butter; stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion, green pepper and salt.
In 3-quart buttered casserole, spread 1/2 the noodles; cover with cheese mixture, then cover this with remaining noodles.
Spoon hamburger mixture on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix all together and put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: pinch pie(low-fat style)
directions: Cook pudding per directions on box; put aside to cool slightly.
Pinch cake into bite size pieces.
In large (7 x 13-inch) pan or bowl,
make a layer of cake pieces (use 1/2 of pieces).
On top of this, put 1/2 of the bananas and 1/2 of the strawberries.
Cover this with 1/2 of the pudding.
Make another layer of cake using the rest of pieces, then layer with fruit and pudding.
Chill for approximately 2 to 3 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place berries and/or bananas on top to decorate if you wish.

title: crisp cucumber pickle
directions: Cover cucumbers with water and pickle lime.
Let stand 12 to 14 hours.
Wash and drain and cover with a strong solution of salt water.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain and wash with fresh water and let stand in fresh water 2 hours.
Make a strong solution of alum and water; put in cucumbers and let come to a boil.
Drain and wash with hot water.
Put pickling spice in cheesecloth and tie so they do not come out.
Combine vinegar and sugar along with the spices.
Put in cucumbers and boil 30 minutes.
Put in jars and let cool before putting top on.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into 4-quart freezer.
Add enough cream to fill freezer 2/3 full (we used 3 pints of cream).
Freeze.
Eat!

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Precook rice and broccoli.
Mix all ingredients into a large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and place sliced cheese on top.
Place in oven again until cheese melts.

title: taco noodle dinner
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook the beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in the water, taco seasoning and salt. Reduce heat; simmer for 2 to 3 minutes. Add mushrooms. Sprinkle noodles over the top. Pour

tomato juice over the noodles and stir gently. Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until noodles are tender. Remove from the heat. Combine the sour cream and parsley; spread over the top. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: veg-all bake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with the cheese, then the crushed crackers.
Melt oleo and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: under-the-sea-pear salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 3/4 cup of syrup.
Coarsely dice pears and set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Add pear syrup and lemon juice.
Measure 1 1/4 cups into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.

title: tealeaf eggs
directions: After eggs are boiled, remove from pot and tap lightly on counter.
Put teabags in the water in pot along with soy sauce. Return eggs to cooking pot; simmer 1-2 hours.
Eggs will have pretty spider web, or leafy pattern when shells are removed.

title: caprese salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine all of the ingredients.
Toss and serve.
Will serve 4. High in vitamins A and C. One of the best sources of lycopene.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup melted butter with 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Pour in bottom of buttered Bundt pan.
Add pecans.
Melt remaining butter and mix with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut rolls in half and dip in butter and sugar mixture.
Roll in 1/2 cup brown sugar.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak dried baby lima beans overnight.
Next day, drain and recover with water and add chopped onion.
Boil until tender. Drain and then combine with sugars and ketchup.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lippy salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Blend tomatoes in blender.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Add tomato mixture to the dissolved Jell-O.
Pour into mold.
Chill. Top with sour cream to serve.
Good with seafood or steaks. Similar to aspic.

title: carrot-nut cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then carrots and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk and cream to boil.
Just before serving, melt butter in saucepan.
Add oysters and juice.
Cook gently just until oysters edges curl.
Add to milk and cream.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: cherry delight cake
directions: Thaw cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix together with mixer. Add slowly sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Slice angel food cake long way.
Put bottom half on cake plate.
Spread with mixture and top with cherry pie filling.
Put top of cake on that and repeat same as bottom.
Chill in box for about 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil eggs and potatoes.
Cool in cold water and dice in quarters.
Cut pickles and celery sticks in small pieces.
Add mayo, mustard and salt.
Add more or less, depending on your desired taste and/or quantity you make.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Spread broccoli in a 9-inch casserole. Dot with cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Mix together and cover with cracker crumbs, then pour remaining 1/4 cup of butter (melted).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef, onions and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce, tomatoes, tomato paste, water, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, basil and oregano. Cover and simmer for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. In a bowl, combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese, egg substitute, salt and pepper.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat; watch to prevent burning.
Stir in the cocoa and sugar in a mixing bowl, then add the melted butter.
Add the eggs and vanilla; stir again. Add the flour and salt; mix until smooth, then add walnuts, if you wish.
Pour batter into a greased 8 or 9-inch pan and spread out even.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until brownies pull away from sides of pan.

title: plantation pecan cookies
directions: Melt margarine in
a saucepan.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Mix sugar with melted margarine.
Beat eggs slightly and add to sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla and flour mixture a little at a time until all is used.
Stir in pecans.
Grease a 13 x 9 pan and add mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: pork salad
directions: Boil Boston butt in water until tender (add water as needed). Chop meat very fine (food processor does great).
Add other chopped ingredients: pecans, bell pepper, celery, onions and salad cubes.
Stir in mayo, salt and pepper to taste.
Add more mayo, if desired.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together except vanilla and butter.
Cook rapidly being careful it does not boil over until soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Set in pan of cold water until consistency of caramel.
Beat hard until mixture thickens and the spoon grates on bottom of the pan.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.
Turn upside down on waxed paper and separate into pieces.
Yield:
16 squares.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in water.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Add flour, then melted margarine; mix.
Spoon into greased muffin pan until half full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Dough will keep
in refrigerator approximately two weeks.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and place in a small ovenproof casserole dish.
Warm for 15 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve with Corn Diggers or Bugles.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix together sugar, Karo, peanuts and dash of salt.
Cook over high heat approximately 10 minutes or until mixture turns light brown and peanuts have popped.
Remove from heat; immediately add soda and stir rapidly.
Pour out onto buttered cookie sheet with rim.
Do not spread or smooth out as this will do away with the air bubbles and make the candy hard instead of brittle and crunchy.

title: brickle bark
directions: Microwave directions:

Line 2 cookie sheets with waxed paper. In 1-quart microwave safe bowl or 4-cup microwave-safe measuring cup, melt almond bark on Medium 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until melted, stirring once halfway through heating.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in half of brickle chips.
Spread mixture on prepared cookie sheet. Repeat, using chocolate-flavored coating and remaining brickle chips.
Refrigerate bark until set.
Break into serving size pieces.
Store in airtight container in cool, dry place.
Yields 1 pound, 10 ounces.

title: wine salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, cherries and wine overnight.
Best to do this at night and stir several times before going to bed.
Next morning, add pineapple (drained), nuts and whipping cream.
This recipe will take a large bowl to mix in.

title: cornbread supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: maureen's mexican dip
directions: Layer cream cheese, chili mixture, cheese and olives.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in 10-inch pie pan.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a flat 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Cook the macaroni in 6 cups of boiling water until tender, but firm to the bite.
Drain and return to pan. Stir in the butter and egg.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix sugar, milk and eggs.
Add flour and vanilla, mixing well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add pineapple.
Layer vanilla wafers and pineapple mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Use a casserole dish or a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Grease lightly with Pam spray.
Crunch up 1 package of crackers and line the bottom of the dish.
In a mixing bowl put green beans, cream of mushroom soup, broccoli and cheese soup, 1 teaspoon of salt and water.
Mix together and pour into dish.
Crunch up the other package of crackers and sprinkle on the top.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: *Pudding, whipped cream, ice cream, sherbet or fresh fruit.

title: veal scallopini(serves 6)
directions: Mix wine with Worcestershire sauce, peeled garlic clove, salad oil, catsup and seasoning.
Cut meat into 2-inch squares.
Wash mushrooms thoroughly.
Marinate steak squares and mushrooms in wine mixture for 2 hour.
Alternate meat squares and mushrooms on skewers.
Broil, turning on all sides, basting frequently with remaining marinade.
Serves 4.

title: easy brulee
directions: Heat cherries until bubbly; drain.
Arrange cherries in the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Spread sour cream over the top.
Sift brown sugar evenly over the surface.
Broil 4 inches from the heat for two minutes or until the sugar is browned and bubbly.
You can serve it immediately or chill it.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: Coat chicken with egg, then roll in cornstarch.
Fry until done; drain.
Heat all fruits and their liquids.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Combine 2 tablespoons cornstarch with water. Stir into flour mixture to thicken.
Add chicken.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creole green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except beans and simmer until celery is tender.
Add beans and cook until tender.

title: chinese-style spinach
directions: Wash and drain spinach, removing any wilted leaves.
Heat oil over high heat.
Add spinach; stir until oil is thoroughly mixed with spinach.
Add seasonings.
Cover; cook for 2 minutes. Garnish with bits of bacon, ham or eggs.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 can French fried onions. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef ball
directions: Food process beef and onions, add other ingredients.
Shape into ball and roll in crushed pecans.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut into serving size pieces.
Pound flour into both sides of steak.
Heat fat in skillet; brown steak on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in single layer in baking dish.
Cover with onion slices.
In skillet, heat tomatoes, loosening skillet drippings.
Add Worcestershire sauce and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour over steak. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.

title: eggplant casserole with ground lamb(moussaka)
directions: Slice eggplant 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 1/2 hour to remove bitterness.
In a skillet, melt 1/4 cup butter and saute onions.
Add the lamb and cook for 10 minutes. Combine parsley, sherry, tomato paste and seasonings.
Stir into meat.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Turn into a bowl. Drain eggplant and dry with paper towels.
Brush eggplant slices with oil and place under broiler until browned on both sides. Grease a large baking pan.
Arrange alternate layers of eggplant and meat mixture in the pan.
Sprinkle each layer with grated Parmesan.
Mix yogurt, eggs, nutmeg and Ricotta cheese.
Pour this sauce on top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 375° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Let stand 1/2 hour before serving.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: candied yams
directions: Pour off syrup and put in baking dish.	Pat with margarine. Mix together sugar, water, vanilla, cinnamon and flour.
Pour over yams.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham-cheese logs
directions: Mix cheese; beat in deviled ham and stir in olives.
Chill. Shape into 2 logs and roll in nuts.

title: italian ricotta pie
directions: In bowl, cream Crisco and sugar by hand.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Add baking powder and flour.
Mix until dough forms ball. Roll half of dough for bottom crust of a 10-inch pie plate.

title: peach dessert
directions: Empty peaches into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Melt oleo and drizzle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate-coconut-pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and butter.
Beat again.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake
until firm (about 45 minutes) at 350°. Freezes well.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; beat on low speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Cover; refrigerate dough 1 to 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.

title: meal pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, meal, flour, sugar and vanilla.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake until shell is done in a 350° oven, then cover with beaten egg whites and brown.

title: potato candy
directions: Combine vanilla and potatoes.
Slowly add sugar to make stiff dough.
Take small portions and roll them out on waxed paper. Spread desired amount of peanut butter, roll in jelly roll fashion.
Cool one hour, cut into small bite size pieces.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix together and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Onion optional.

title: fruit squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add 1 egg at a time; beat. Then add flour and vanilla. Place nuts in bottom of pan; put batter on nuts and spread lightly. Place fruits, that have been chopped and mixed, on top of the batter. Press into batter with back of spoon. Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven. When cool, cut into squares.

title: barbecued ham
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham in skillet.
Let simmer until sugar dissolves.
Add ham.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: squash puppies
directions: Beat egg; add buttermilk, onion and squash.
Combine corn meal and flour; add to squash mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into deep hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Drain vegetables and mix together.
Add vinegar and sugar. Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients with butter.
Add flour and mustard and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter for 7 minutes. Add eggs and flour. Add lemon juice, vanilla and salt. Bake 1 hour at 350° in a tube pan.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick pizza breadsticks
directions: Lightly grease a large baking sheet. Unroll pizza dough onto baking sheet (9 x 13-inch).

Brush the dough with melted butter after you have pressed the dough down. In a large bowl, combine the cheese, Italian seasoning, garlic powder and red pepper. Sprinkle over dough. Using a sharp knife, cut dough into 24 strips. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with pizza sauce.

title: stromboli bread
directions: Thaw bread overnight.
Spread out on cookie sheet.
Mix and spread ingredients, (except meat & cheese) on dough.
Cover with cheese and meat and roll up like jelly roll.
Place seam side down on greased cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish, 8 x 10-inch with 1 stick melted butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ann's lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon jello with boiling water.
Refrigerate until cool. Mix sugar and cream cheese together until smooth.
Add lemon jello and lemon juice; mix.
Refrigerate until pie is congealed.	May freeze this pie.

title: slumgullion
directions: Brown the ground beef with onion and pepper.
Drain grease. Drain liquid from peas and corn.
Place in a casserole dish.
Add tomato sauce, salt, Velveeta, meat, onion and pepper.
Mix well. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: Cook like pancakes, about 4 inches in diameter in nonstick frypan sprayed with Pam.
Cook until golden on both sides.
Makes 6 to 8 rounds.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together.
Grease (butter) pan and crust with sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool in pan for 1 hour.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and pat in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix last 3 ingredients well and pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican dish
directions: Melt butter in a skillet. Add onion and saute over low heat until a delicate brown. Add cucumbers and water.
Cook until water is absorbed and cucumbers browned.
Mix sour cream, egg yolk, sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add to cucumbers and cook slowly until mixture begins to boil.
Serves 4.

title: corn cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Melt margarine in frying pan. Dip the corn mixture into the pan and fry as you do pancakes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Let cool then add 3 pkg yeast with 1 c warm water.
Stir in flour and knead.

title: party mix snacks
directions: Melt
margarine.
Add
garlic
salt, celery salt, table salt, Tabasco
sauce
and
Worcestershire sauce; mix with all ingredients and bake 2 hours at 200° or until crisp.
Store in airtight
containers.
(This is great at Christmastime.) Makes large amount.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve candies in water over low heat, then add 1 tablespoon lemon juice, jello and applesauce.
Make the cream cheese into little balls and add when thickening.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Mix tomato soup with enough water added to make 2 cups.
Heat and add the cream cheese; beat well with mixer.
Add lemon jello; let cool, but not congeal.
Add celery, pepper and onion.
Add salad dressing and refrigerate.

title: soul sister punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill pitcher (one gallon) with water. Serve over ice.

title: fluffernutter brownies
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions and add in peanut butter chips.
Pour into a greased 8x8 baking dish.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and bake 15 minutes.
Remove and top with marshmallows and return to oven for 3-5 more minutes.
Cool and cut into 12 pieces.

title: deer stick
directions: Mix well and let stand 3 days refrigerated in a sealed container.
Knead every day for 5 minutes.
Bake for 9 hours at 160°.
Turn over at 4 1/2 hours.
Bake on a cookie sheet.
Drain on paper towels when through.

title: pastel patties
directions: Beat Karo, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Mix in confectioners sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Tint with food color.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch patties.
Top patties with nut halves.
Makes 48.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse and drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Toss spaghetti, milk and eggs.
Put mixture into pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top, then add a layer of pepperoni and enough cheese to cover top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Mix apples and cinnamon together; put into baking dish.
Mix flour, brown sugar and butter together until mixed.
Put over the top of the apples, then bake at 350° for 1 hour or until apples are done.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: italian chicken
directions: You will need a Reynolds oven cooking bag (large size).

title: chocolate fudge pies
directions: Beat egg yolks with half of sugar and melted margarine.
Mix the other half of sugar, cocoa and flour with a little hot water (about 1/4 cup) just to blend together.
Put the 2 mixtures together and mix thoroughly.
Add milk, salt and vanilla; this mixture will be thin.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake until firm (30 to 40 minutes) at 325°.
Cool pies, then cover with meringue. Serve warm or cold.

title: egg nog
directions: How to make:
Place all ingredients into a blender, mix.
Pour into glasses, garnish with nutmeg.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together;
add broccoli last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter-scalloped potatoes
directions: In 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, arrange 1/3 of potatoes. Dot with 1/3 of butter; dash with salt and pepper.
Repeat with two more layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 425° about 40 minutes.
To brown, uncover last 10 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and peel.
Cool and slice in thin slices.
Cut bacon in small pieces and fry. Then add flour, 1/2 cup water, vinegar and sugar.
Let thicken.
Add salt and pepper; pour mixture over potatoes.
Add pickles, onion and celery.
Serve warm or cold.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Add shortening and eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla and melted cooking chocolate.
Blend well; gently stir in nuts.
Turn into lightly greased pan and bake about 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and immediately cover with chocolate bits and marshmallows.
Allow to stand several minutes until soft and gently spread over entire mix with the back of a fork.
Cool before cutting.

title: zwiebel kuchen(onion pie)
directions: Sift flour and salt together; cut in shortening.
Mix in water with swift strokes.
Roll out dough and put into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.

title: cream cheese cutout cookies
directions: Combine butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Cream together.
Add egg, vanilla and extract.
Blend in flour and baking powder. Refrigerate for several hours.
Cut out.
Bake at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut up squash, steam and drain.
In a bowl, mix medium onion, large jar pimento, small green pepper and box of grated Velveeta cheese.
Mix in crumbs and butter.
Beat 4 eggs with 1 cup milk; pour over mixture which has been put into casserole or baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: party dream salad
directions: In a small mixing bowl beat together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar,
lemon
juice
and
salt until light and fluffy. Fold
in bananas, drained pineapple, oranges, cherries, pecans and whipped cream.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with cherries.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Wash squash and cut 3/4-inch cubes.
Cook in a saucepan with onion in a small amount of salted water until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Drain and place in a casserole.
In a bowl, mix egg, pepper, milk, butter, salt, crumbs and 1 cup cheese.
Pour over squash and lightly blend.
Sprinkle with remaining cup of cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: grandma's gingersnaps
directions: Mix together all ingredients in the order listed.
Form dough into balls the size of a nickel.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
If desired, shake in bag of powdered sugar while still warm.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together with wire whip the sugar, cocoa, flour and salt. Mix into dry ingredients the milk.
Microwave 2 minutes and then whip.
Microwave 1 minute and then whip.
Continuing microwaving and whipping until desired consistency.
Stir in butter, vanilla and almond extract.

title: christmas candy
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk.
Cook to 238° on candy thermometer, or soft ball.
Stir in Marshmallow Creme and beat until mixture is thick and creamy.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour onto greased platter.
Let set until firm.
Cut with a warm knife into bite size pieces.
Makes about 100 pieces.

title: pecan candy
directions: Heat nuts, sugar and butter in heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly until nuts are toasted and sugar is golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread nuts on a salted sheet of aluminum foil; sprinkle with salt.
Cool.
Break into 2 or 3 nut clusters.

title: mocha cakes
directions: Prepare cake mix following directions for cupcakes. Fill cupcake tins halfway. Cook according to package directions and let cool 1 hour.
Remove cupcakes from tins and spread only the sides of the cakes with raspberry jam. Sprinkle shredded coconut over jam.

title: fettucine with cheese and cream
directions: Cook fettucine as directed on package; drain.
Heat margarine and whipping cream over low heat until margarine is melted.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over hot noodles, stirring until noodles are well coated.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: a good dessert
directions: Crumble and press into bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° and cool completely.

title: extra special potatoes
directions: In large bowl, mix well first 4 ingredients.
Thaw hash browns and stir in.
Place in 12 x 8-inch casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt. Cook until clear. Cool. Beat egg whites until frothy. Continue beating while pouring in cooked mixture. Beat 5 minutes. Cover pie, sealing edges to crust. Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter until particles are fine.
Add egg, cream and vanilla. Blend thoroughly.
Dough may be refrigerated, if desired.
Roll out on floured pastry cloth or board to 1/8-inch thickness. Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes, until delicately browned.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes in a large saucepan with 4 cups of water. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Add milk and vegetables to drained potatoes.
Bring to a gentle boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese, butter and seasoning to taste.
Heat over low heat, stirring frequently until cheese is melted and vegetables are tender-crisp.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Place cream cheese in medium glass mixing bowl.
Microwave about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on Medium-high (Roast), or until softened. Add mayonnaise, onions and parsley; stir.
Add next 5 ingredients. Microwave 4 to 6 minutes on Medium-high or until hot.
Good served in shepherd's bread.
Use bread scooped from bread to dip with.

title: almond bacon cheese ball
directions: Mix bacon, cheese, green onion, mayonnaise and salt. Cover mix with diced almonds. Place in covered container and chill. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten egg; add baking powder.
Chill and slice.
Mix cinnamon and sugar; add vanilla with small	amount	water.	Brush
tops of cookies with pastry brush.
Sprinkle
on
cinnamon
and
sugar	mix.
Top with nut half.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream first three ingredients.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt one 12 ounce bag chocolate chips and a small piece of paraffin in a double boiler and dip balls to coat.

title: chili-pepper quiche
directions: Slit chilies; spread open.
Pat dry with absorbent towels. Sprinkle cheese over chilies.
In bowl, combine soup, cream and eggs.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: cornflake pork chops
directions: Crumble cornflakes; spread sour cream over pork chops, then roll in cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in brown paper bag and shake to mix.
Add chicken and shake to coat.
Remove chicken and reserve remaining flour mixture.
In a large skillet, warm 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Brown chicken on one side, then add remaining oil and brown other side.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add margarine to skillet and add onions, cooking until soft.

title: baked stuffed eggplant boats
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into quarters lengthwise.
Slice part of the way into center of wedge, making a pocket for stuffing.
Place on oiled baking sheet.
Brush with oil and broil until browned.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine together; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 7 minutes in a 350° oven. Refrigerate.
Blend together the cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Top with the cherry pie filling.
Keep refrigerated.

title: carob pudding
directions: Mix everything into a saucepan or double boiler except the vanilla.
Stir over medium heat until the pudding begins to bubble (about 15 minutes).
Stir constantly to prevent lumps.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour into individual dishes to cool. Serve plain or with milk or whipped cream.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine oleo, brown sugar, pineapple slices and cloves and put into a loaf baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and put meat mixture on ingredients in loaf pan.
When you invert the pan after baking you have a glaze on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger-rice
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, 3/4 cup Minute rice, mustard, salt and pepper.
Roll in balls.
Add tomato soup, 1 can water and 3/4 cup Minute rice.
Pressure in pressure cooker for 10 minutes.

title: raspberry vinegar
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar to boiling. Add raspberries and cool. After 48 hours, strain through a coffee filter. Bottle and add a few fresh raspberries. Use this in potato salad, salad dressings and marinades for beef, chicken and seafood.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together; bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: quick shrimp chowder
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven, over medium heat, add onion and saute for 8 minutes or until tender.
Stir in cream of potato soup, milk, and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp, reduce heat and simmer, stirring often for 5 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Garnish with parsley and serve with oyster crackers if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 12 cups.

title: crockpot stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; drain well.
Combine in medium bowl the ground beef, rice, onion, salt, and ketchup.
Mix well. Stuff peppers 2/3 full.
Arrange stuffed peppers in crock-pot. Combine tomato soup, tomato sauce, and water; pour over peppers.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Pour tomato sauce from crockpot into gravy bowl to pour over peppers when serving.
Sprinkle with cheese if desired.

title: easy mexican dinner
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
In mixing bowl, combine beans, taco sauce, tomato sauce and onion.
Set aside 1 cup of corn chips and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Add remaining Cheddar cheese and corn chips to bean mixture.
Then add meat to mixture. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: fried pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops in skillet until brown on both sides.
Place pork chops in casserole dish, cut up onion.
Pour tomato soup over top of pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix well by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: bird nest
directions: Cream together all ingredients, except egg whites and chopped nuts; put in fridge until you can work with it.
Roll into egg whites, then roll in chopped nuts.
Use thumbprint to fill with Solo filling.

title: overnight layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in large bowl.
Sprinkle a handful of grated cheese on top.
Cover tightly and let set overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Toss lightly just before serving.

title: brown sugar date and nut bread
directions: Mix soda with chopped dates.
Pour boiling water over dates. Allow to cool.
Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add beaten egg, vanilla and salt.
Pour off water from dates and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour and nuts.
Lastly, add dates and put in loaf pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger. Fix hamburger as taco packet suggests.
Chop onion fine.
Shred lettuce.
Chop tomatoes.
Put Doritos in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except taco sauce and Cheez Whiz.
Serve with taco sauce and Cheez Whiz.

title: cracker jack corn
directions: Mix sugar, butter, syrup and salt together in large glass dish.
Cook on High until it has boiled for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in baking soda; mix well.
Pour over popcorn and coat well.
Cook 3 minutes in paper sack, shaking every 30 seconds. Store in an airtight container.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: In frypan, cook onion and hamburger.
Drain grease off.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot tacos
directions: Stir together meat and taco seasoning mix in crock-pot.
Add milk, cheese, beans, chili, tomatoes and spices.
Cook on low all day long.

title: yum yum balls
directions: Melt together butter and sugar.
Add dates and coconut.
Cook 6 minutes only.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: skillet hash
directions: Combine beef, potatoes, onion, parsley, salt ad pepper.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Spread meat mixture in skillet. Brown hash 10 to 15 minutes, turning frequently with wide spatula. Stir in water.
Cover; reduce heat and cook 10 minutes or until crisp. Makes 4 servings.

title: bird nests
directions: Melt morsels over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat. Stir in noodles, peanuts and pecans.
Drop onto wax paper.
Let stand until set.

title: honeymoon chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serves 2.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost.

title: homemade beef stew
directions: In crock-pot add desired amount of extra lean beef stew, potatoes, carrots, onions and one can of mixed vegetables (if desired).
Add one can tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste and any other spices you wish.
Stir well.
Cover and cook while you are at work.

title: liz's vichyssoise
directions: Combine broth and vegetables in a heavy saucepan.
Simmer 40 to 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Cool slightly.
Place mixture, in batches, in a blender and blend until smooth.
Pour into a large bowl.
Add half and half, pepper and salt to taste. Cover and chill until served.
Garnish with chopped chives or finely chopped green onion tops, if desired.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix the dry ingredients in a two-quart saucepan.
Add milk and stir.
Place on medium heat.
Stir constantly until it begins to boil.
Do not stir while boiling.
Allow to boil 10 to 15 minutes. As mixture boils low in pan, place a very small (tiny) amount of mixture in 1/2 ounce of cold water.
When it forms a soft ball, the fudge is done.
Keep testing to avoid overcooking.
Remove from heat.
Allow to stand for about 5 minutes.
Add butter, peanut butter and marshmallows.
Beat by hand until starts to thicken.
Add vanilla.
Beat until it turns from shiny to dull. Do not overbeat as it will become sugary.
Pour into a buttered platter or container of your choice.
Allow to cool at room temperature.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Crush zwieback and mix together with sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Line a spring-form pan with mixture, just bottom.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Layer ingredients
in
order
listed:
Mash avocado and mix with mayonnaise
and lemon juice for first layer.
Combine taco mix and sour
cream,
mixing well for second layer.
Then layer onion, tomato
and cheese; top with black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.
A	9
x
5-inch dish works well for this recipe. Do not prepare far in advance.

title: beans and beef bake
directions: Brown meat with onions and peppers.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Place tomatoes in pie shell.
Mix salt, pepper, basil and onions and sprinkle over tomatoes.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese and spread evenly over all.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: date cake
directions: Cut up dates, pineapple, cherries, and nuts.
Dredge with a little of the flour and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar, add beaten eggs, flour sifted with baking soda and salt, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour over fruit and mix well.
Bake in a paper-lined tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 275 degrees.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mix well.
Mix eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef drumsticks
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup crumbs and green peppers.
Shape 1/2 cup meat mixture around metal or wood skewers. Roll drumsticks in 1/2 cup fine crumbs.
Melt 4 to 5 tablespoons of Crisco in a heavy 8 or 9-inch frying pan.
Fry drumsticks, turning to brown all over.
Cover frying pan and cook about 15 minutes or until cooked through.
Serve with pan-fried green pepper rings. Cut peppers into thin crosswise slices.
Remove seeds; fry in a little Crisco until lightly browned.
Makes 6.

title: easy cake
directions: Pour 2 tablespoons of melted margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer over melted margarine, pie filling, cake mix, coconut and pecans.
Pour remaining margarine over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pineapple drops
directions: Make your own favorite oatmeal cookie recipe.
Substitute the liquid in your recipe with crushed pineapple and its juice.
(If your recipe calls for 1 cup water, substitute 1/2 cup crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup pineapple juice.) Bake for the time and temperature called for in your favorite recipe.

title: greg's favorite enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning according to package directions.
In a separate pan make Spanish Rice-A-Roni, using Mexican stewed tomatoes.
When rice is done, add about 1/2 of it to taco meat.
Mix in cheese, reserving enough to sprinkle on top.
Roll mixture into tortillas.
Place in sprayed 13 x 9-inch pan, seam side down.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: flavored oyster crackers
directions: Spread crackers in large roasting pan.
Mix all ingredients. Pour over crackers and mix well.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Mix every 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Store in tight container.
Will last up to 2 weeks.
Makes great snacking!

title: bacon and tomato vegetable dip
directions: Stir together cream cheese, mustard and celery salt.
Stir in bacon, tomato and green pepper.
Cover and chill.
Serve.
Makes 2 cups.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Broil for 7 minutes on one side; turn and broil 5 minutes on the other side.
Slice very thin.

title: pineapple-bacon pastries
directions: On floured surface, roll each thawed patty shell to a 9-inch circle.
Spread bacon lightly with mustard.
Top each circle with 1 bacon slice and 1 pineapple slice.
Halve cheese slices; crisscross atop pineapple.
Moisten edges of each patty shell. Fold two opposite sides to center, overlapping slightly.
Then fold other 2 sides to center, pinching edges to seal.
Prick or slit tops.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Makes 6.

title: cheese-olive anchovy spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: in a hurry cake
directions: *Fruit of your choice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Have pie shell baked.
Combine sugar, flour and cocoa and sift together real good.
This keeps your pie from lumping.
Slowly add milk, eggs and butter.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with egg whites.
Brown egg whites.

title: burns baked beans
directions: Mix beans and put in a 9 X 13 pan.

title: stained glass candy
directions: Boil mixture to 300° using candy thermometer.
Add coloring while boiling.
Remove from heat; add flavoring.
Pour mixture immediately into large bread pan with thick layer of confectioners sugar.
(Rinse down sides of pan with very hot water before candy hardens onto sides.)
Test corners to begin cutting with kitchen scissors.
Need at least two people to cut candy onto waxed paper before it becomes too hardened.
After cutting into bite size pieces, place in wire basket to shake off excess powdered sugar. Place in airtight containers.

title: cool cosmo
directions: Fill cocktail shaker with ice.
Pour juice almost to the top. Add 2 - 3 shots of lemon or raspberry flavored vodka and a small squeeze of lime.
Shake.
Serve in chilled martini glass with a slice of lime.

title: mexican hush puppies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoons in deep, hot oil, until brown.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut up fruits and nuts; add all ingredients.
Bake in huge pan at 300° until done.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Chop chicken and put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Tear tortillas and layer on chicken. Mix other ingredients together and pour over meat and tortillas. Put cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spatini
directions: Fry sausage; do not drain.
Put onion and pepper in saucepan with a small amount of water.
Cook; drain.
Cook noodles as directed.
In large pot, add Ragu, noodles and rest of ingredients except cheese.
Cook on simmer until hot.
Make cheese into balls. Place into sauce and noodles.
Place rest of cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potato and boil until very soft.
Drain water and mash potato.
Next, begin to add powdered sugar to potato until it feels like dough.
Roll out with rolling pin like a pie shell. Spread a thin layer of peanut butter over the dough.
Begin to roll the dough up.
Should come out to be the size of a half dollar.
Wrap in wax paper, then in foil and place in freezer until ready to use.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Cut muffins in quarters.
Arrange on cookie sheets.
Drain crab meat well.
Combine all other ingredients and mix well. Spread mixture on muffins.
Freeze at least 30 minutes.
Broil until bubbly and golden brown.
These can be frozen and used at a later date.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add melted butter, peanut butter and vanilla. Spread in buttered pan and refrigerate.

title: homemade farmer's cheese(cottage cheese)
directions: *If you want low calorie cheese, use low-fat milk.

title: mexican bake
directions: Melt shortening in skillet; add onion, ground beef and seasonings.
Break up meat and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add corn and tomatoes and bring to boil, breaking up tomatoes with spoon.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Stir up hush puppy mix according to package directions, then spoon over meat mixture.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 nice servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake and cool cake mix according to directions (except use margarine instead of cooking oil).
Break one layer of cake in small pieces and put in punch bowl.
Spread 1 package of instant vanilla pudding (prepared according to package directions) over cake.
Place 1 pint of strawberries over pudding.
Pour 1/2 of warm Jell-O (prepared with 2 cups of hot water) over strawberries. Spread 1 carton of Cool Whip over Jell-O.
Repeat ending with Cool Whip.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and melted margarine.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm in center.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Melt butter in large pan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add food coloring.
Stir in corn flakes.
Stir until well coated with butter.
Finger-shape into individual wreaths.
Dot with candies. Will also make 1 large wreath.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces and brown in hot fat.
Brown onions in fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake, uncovered, in oven at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick squash casserole
directions: Boil, drain and mash squash to make 4 cups mix with soup mix, pimento and sour cream.
Bake in a greased casserole dish for 20 to 30 minutes.
May top with grated cheese or bread crumbs.

title: hopping john soup(for new year's day)
directions: Cook peas in water; season to taste.
Cook sausage and drain grease.
Add sausage to peas and cook.
Saut celery and onions in butter just until onions are clear.
Add to peas and sausage.
Add rice in the last hour of cooking soup.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.

title: two story fudge
directions: Blend 1/4 cup of melted butter and cocoa in medium bowl until smooth and set aside.
Place peanut butter chips in second medium bowl and set aside.
Combine sugar, marshmallow cream, milk and 1/4 cup butter in a heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Immediately add 1/2 of hot mixture to chips, stirring until melted.
Spread this mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch foil lined pan.
Stir the rest of the hot mixture into the cocoa mixture.
Allow to cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss and spread evenly over the top of the peanut butter layer.
Cool and remove from pan and foil.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: ken's mai tai's
directions: Mix all ingredients in a half gallon container and add 2 tablespoons powdered sugar. Shake well. Place in refrigerator. Best if made several days before using.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: Prepare chicken with taco seasoning as directed on package of taco seasoning mix; cool 10 minutes. Stir in salsa, beans, corn and 1 cup cheese. Spread 1/4 cup enchilada sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Place 2/3 cup chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up. Place in dish seam side down, on top of sauce.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce over tortillas; sprinkle with remaining cheese and the sliced ripe olives. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and filling is hot.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Line pan
with	corn
tortillas.
Mix
chicken,
soups, olives, chilies and
tomatoes
and green chilies and pour into pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: seafoam punch
directions: Place sugar and water in large punch bowl.
Add soft drink powder and stir until powder dissolves.
Add vanilla ice cream, one spoonful at a time.
Pour in the carbonated beverages, resting the bottle on rim of bowl.
Serve immediately.
Yields 16 servings.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix beaten eggs and the next 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Press into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Combine in order given. Roll in balls and press down with sugared glass with design on the bottom or chill for 2 hours and roll out for cut-out cookies.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. When edges turn just slightly brown, remove from the oven.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain, peel and slice.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Saute minced onion in bacon fat until softened.
Add bacon and onion to potatoes.
Add vinegar and water to drippings and bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes and add salt, pepper and sour cream.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and put in plastic storage container.
Use 1/3 cup of mixture per 1 cup of hot water.

title: jelly-roll cake
directions: In small bowl of electric mixer, let eggs warm to room temperature, about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease the bottom of 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, then line the bottom with waxed paper.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix
the
first
six ingredients well, in order listed. Add chocolate chips and German chocolate.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: baked oatmeal(an amish recipe)
directions: In a large bowl, mix the three wet items. In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients to the wet mixture and gently blend, until the dry mix is moistened. Bake in a lightly greased, 9x9 pan for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed.
Add tuna, soups, peas and curry powder; mix well.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Heat 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat tortillas 5 seconds. Spread mixture on tortillas and roll them up.
Refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
Slice them cold.
Serve with salsa on the side.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Add other ingredients and place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nestle's holiday fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring vigorously.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir vigorously 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan lined with foil.
Chill.
Cut into squares.

title: beef and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Brown meat with onion. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda. Combine butter, sugars, pudding mix, and vanilla in a large mixing bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy. Beat in eggs; add flour mixture then stir in chips and nuts. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: grape salad
directions: This makes a green salad.
It can be made ahead of time and kept in the refrigerator.
Can also add green cake coloring to make a deeper color.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add oil, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour or spoon into cupcake baking papers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lemony shrimp salad
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add shrimp and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until just cooked through but not overcooked.
Taste to test. Drain. Run under cold water and pat dry.
Place shrimp in a bowl with grapes and radishes.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Add beaten egg.
Mix other ingredients. Pour into large bowl and store, covered, in refrigerator about 45 minutes to rise.
Spoon into greased or buttered muffin pans. Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: creamy dijon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Serve chilled over your favorite salad greens or vegetables.
"0 fat."

title: my wedding punch
directions: Mix lemon juice and sugar together.
When ready to serve, mix all ingredients together, adding sherbet last.
Serves 50.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tura's pickles
directions: Boil together vinegar, sugar and salt.
Mix and pour over cucumbers, onion and pepper.
Let stand overnight.
Can be refrigerated 3 to 4 months.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat together mashed bananas and butter until creamy.
Add eggs and water; beat well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Add chopped walnuts.
Spoon batter into an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Cook and cut into squares.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar; cream together well.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour before measuring; add spices and cocoa and sift again.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture alternately to egg mixture, beating after each addition.
Lightly dredge nuts and raisins in small amount of flour and chop.
Add nuts, raisins and jam, stirring to blend.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick, stirring constantly; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp; heat through.
Serve over hot rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Take small balls of dough and roll; flatten slightly.
Bake at 350°.
If cookies don't crack, there's not enough flour.
Should have appearance of boughten cookies.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, beating light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; add vanilla, dry ingredients, zucchini, coconut and chopped nuts.
Spread mixture into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (check at 30 minutes).
Frost while warm.

title: grandma's hot dish
directions: Pour soup in casserole dish.
Brown meat and salt and pepper to taste.
Add the potatoes and carrots.
Mix together.
Put 1/2 on top of soup.
Add 1/4 cup green beans, then hamburger mixture, then 1/4 cup green beans.
Top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° with lid.
Serves 6.

title: turmeric vegetables
directions: *Cherry tomatoes, zucchini, summer squash, onions separated into rings, cucumbers and carrots can be used.

title: fudge
directions: Mix thoroughly in medium saucepan all ingredients.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour into pan and cool.
Nuts can be added.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Arrange pork chops in a 9 x 13 cake pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Make dressing and put on top of chops. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: breaded veal cutlets sicilian style
directions: Combine
cracker
crumbs with cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Dip veal cutlets first in eggs, then in cracker crumb mixture,
coating
well.
Heat
oil
in
a
large skillet; add cutlets and fry until golden.
Add more oil if necessary.

title: chicken and dumpling stew
directions: Boil chicken breasts in salted water to cover until meat is tender.
Remove from broth.
Reserve broth and cut chicken from bone.
Return to broth.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, vanilla, oil and water.
Bake in greased sheet cake pan for 25 or 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: "healthy treat" popsicles
directions: Place milk, sugar, Kool-Aid, dry milk and water in blender. Chop 30 seconds until foamy.
Add ice cubes (as many as you can fit into blender).
Chop until ice is fine.
(At this point, you have a "Slurpee".)

title: pink salad
directions: Stir in dry jello, Cool Whip and cottage cheese in a large bowl.
Drain pineapple and add to the mixture.
Stir well.
May be eaten immediately.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: california baked beans
directions: In large pot or crock-pot, add baked beans, lima beans and kidney beans, drained.
Saute onions until clear and add to beans. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
If baking, cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
In crock-pot, start on high then turn to low 3 to 4 hours.

title: vinegar cobbler
directions: Bring vinegar, water and sugar to boil. Mix flour, salt and baking powder together. Add oil and enough milk to make soft dough. Roll dough thin; cut into 1-inch strips, reserving enough to cover top of cobbler. Break strips into small pieces as they are dropped into boiling liquid. Boil 2 or 3 minutes. Pour into deep dish. Cover with crust to fit. Cut vents. Brush with melted margarine and sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 425° until top is browned.

title: fresh salsa
directions: In a food processor with steel blade running, drop in garlic and coriander.
Pulse peppers and onion until coarsely chopped. Pulse in tomato.
Place in bowl.
Stir in vinegar, salt and hot sauce.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Cover with soup. Sprinkle with onion mix.
Cover tight with foil.
Bake at 400° for 55 minutes.
Uncover and pour off gravy.
Brown chicken uncovered, if desired.
Serve gravy over rice.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix and form into balls. Pour 1 can tomatoes over them or 1 pint tomato juice and bake 2 to 3 hours.

title: raisin safari cookies
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes. Drain well.
Beat butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, butter, and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup cool whip and powdered sugar and spread on crust. Mix instant pudding with milk.
Beat 2 minutes until thick. Spread on cream cheese layer.
Top with cool whip.
Can be topped with chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: indian corn stew
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter for 5 minutes.
Add meat and brown, stirring frequently. Add corn, soup, sugar and salt. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in flour, blended with water. Cook for a few minutes and then serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Make white sauce by using 2 tablespoons of the melted oleo and blending it with the flour, milk and pepper.
Cook until thickened; add corn, sugar and salt; mix well.
Combine bread crumbs with the remaining melted oleo.
Cover the bottom of the baking dish with a layer of the corn mixture.
Sprinkle a heavy layer of crumbs over corn.
Add remaining corn and top with crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over casserole when taken out of oven.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper; remove all seeds, wash insides and cook in boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Set aside 1 cup of cake mix for topping.
Add egg to remaining cake mix with melted margarine.
Pat this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: billygoat cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Mix baking soda in water, stir into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and flour, mix well.
Fold in dates, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for about 10 minutes, or until light brown.
These stay moist and chewy.

title: shatley springs slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; add more seasoning if needed.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: easy pepperoni pizza roll
directions: Let yeast bread rise.
Flour wax paper and roll out bread. Spread pizza sauce and add pepperoni slices and cheese.
Roll bread up in an oblong roll; tuck ends under pizza roll.
