Place in a buttered pan; butter the top of the pizza roll.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve Jell-O in the hot water and set aside.
Beat on medium, cake mix, eggs and oil until smooth. Add Jell-O mixture and beat well.
Pour into a greased tube pan and bake until done.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat together the cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread on cake.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, green pepper and rice.
Shape into balls.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine soup and water and pour over meatballs.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: low-fat tuna
directions: Drain tuna well.
Mix all remaining ingredients and chill. Low-fat tuna is good with crackers or on a sandwich.

title: christmas dressing
directions: In heavy skillet, saute celery, onion and green pepper until tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water; pour over bread crumbs and cornbread in large bowl.
Add sauteed vegetables.
Brown sausage in heavy skillet and add to bread mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients with mixture; toss lightly to mix well.
Form into 2-inch balls and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Garnish turkey platter with the balls.

title: ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and dry Ranch dressing until well blended. Spread 1/4 of the cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Sprinkle pimientos, diced green chilies and green onions over cream cheese mixture.
Roll up tortillas tightly and chill 2 hours.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices and lay slices on cut side.
Arrange on serving tray.
Makes a great holiday appetizer due to its red and green colors.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Drain off grease.
Place dough in ungreased large pizza pan.
Press over bottom and up sides.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with thawed potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together in a bowl.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese, olives and bacon bits on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave ham vegetable bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetable in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Mix well and cover with glass lid.
Microwave for 30 minutes on High.
Add vegetable and re-cover.
Continue cooking for 8 to 10 minutes on High.
Stir to combine vegetables.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Add potatoes, carrots and onion; cook until tender.
Drain well.
Add peas and chicken.
Put in a buttered 2-quart casserole.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on a cookie sheet into a flat rectangle. Bake until light brown.
Combine cream cheese, salad dressing and green onions.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with raw vegetables.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Cut in squares of desired size and serve.

title: peanut butter brownie treats
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches or line with paper baking cups.
Melt chocolate chips and margarine in 2-quart saucepan over low heat. Stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until smooth; stir in vanilla.
Beat in remaining ingredients except frosting until smooth.
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until tops are dry.
Cool; spread with frosting.
Decorate each with a miniature peanut butter cup, if desired.
Makes 12 brownies.

title: shrimp or crawfish rice cooker style
directions: Place all ingredients in the rice cooker and stir until distributed.
Cook as if you were cooking rice in your rice cooker.
Do not open and stir during cooking process.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Combine ingredients and kneed 1 to 2 minutes.
Roll out to 1/2 to 3/4 inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450 degrees 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in pot.
Add vanilla.
In a 6-quart pot (a pressure cooker works great) pour milk over the sugar.
Put this on high heat and stir constantly.
Once it boils, reduce heat a bit and boil for 6 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter, chocolate morsels and then nuts.
Stir until thoroughly blended. Pour in a 13 x 17-inch pan.
Let stand overnight (covered.)

title: layered gazpacho salad
directions: Sprinkle 1/3 of croutons over bottom of a 2-quart casserole. Layer 1/2 of the following ingredients: tomatoes, cucumbers, onion, green pepper and celery.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and Lawry's salt and spread 1/2 of mixture over top.
Repeat layers, ending with last 1/3 of croutons.
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Serves 8 to 10.
(Prepare the day ahead.)

title: chocolate cherry upside-down cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling over bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add all liquid ingredients at once.
Stir to moisten and pour over cherry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and invert, then cool.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with other ingredients and form into balls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 86 balls.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Pour buttermilk mixture over sugar and cook (stirring constantly) until soft ball forms in ice water.
Add vanilla.
Let cool 1 minute.
Add pecans and mix well.
When mixture begins to cream, drop on waxed paper.

title: layered garden salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight before serving.

title: blackberry pudding
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Put in flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Stir good.
Pour berries on top, then 1 cup sugar and 2 cups water.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: tasty fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows and fruit mix lightly.
Chill and serve.
Variations:
Substitute 11 ounce can mandarin orange slices drained for orange sections and omit cinnamon.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour a layer over butter.
Add a layer of peaches, then a layer of mixture and another layer of peaches.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°. Serve with whipped cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the rest of the ingredients and mix together.
Chill.

title: quick and easy ambrosia
directions: In a bowl, add mixed fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Slice bananas and mix in right before serving.

title: crab giovanni
directions: Saute green pepper and mushrooms in butter.
Combine with rest of ingredients, reserving cheese for top of casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Beat the egg yolks into the cream.
Melt butter in pan and saute lobster meat for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and add wine, then cook for 3 minutes more.
Add cream and egg mixture, stirring tenderly, until sauce thickens.
Add cognac; stir and serve over hot, buttered toast points.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets. Peel, then shred. Stir in sour cream, onions, 1 cup cheese, salt and pepper. Turn into greased 2-quart casserole. Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fried chicken breasts
directions: Cut boneless chicken breasts in halves; roll in flour and pound both sides with meat tenderizing utensil.
Cover with milk and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Make crust by pressing separated crescent rolls onto a 12 x 16-inch cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes in 400° oven.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix thoroughly. Spread over crust.
Top with vegetables.
Cut into small bite-sized pieces and serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, chopped chestnuts, onion and soup mix.
Drain spinach and squeeze dry; add spinach to mix. Scoop out long loaf of French bread.
Fill center with dip.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In a 4-quart crock-pot, combine potatoes, water, onion, bouillon granules and pepper.
Cook on low for 9 to 11 hours or on high 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Stir cheese and milk into soup. Cover and cook on low for 1 hour.

title: baklava
directions: Combine 2 cups sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Brush 12 x 17-inch baking tray or pan with melted butter.
Place 12 phyllo leaves at bottom, brushing each with melted butter.
Spread 1/2 of nut mixture on leaves.
Add another layer with 6 buttered leaves and add remaining nut mixture on top.
Finish with a top layer of 12 to 15 buttered leaves.
Score top with sharp knife into diamond shapes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.
Let cool, then pour syrup over until saturated.

title: strawberry congealed salad(sugar-free)
directions: Wash, cap and cut strawberries in small pieces.
Drain.
In a small bowl, sprinkle strawberries with Equal.
Let stand a few minutes before adding cold water.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Cut spareribs into pieces of about 3 ribs each.
Brown slowly so that ribs cook a little while browning.

Mix all ingredients and place in covered baking dish large enough to hold spareribs. Place ribs, upside down, on sauerkraut so they will cook well. Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and turn chops upright.
Return to oven for 1/2 hour.
Chops should be tender and brown.
Meaty ribs may require longer baking. Makes 4 servings.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a fork; make a small hole in the middle, then add the water, vinegar, vanilla and oil.
Mix with a fork.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Bring to a boil water and sugar; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add jello.
In large container, add diluted orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice, processed bananas, strawberries, boiled sugar and jello mix.
Freeze for at least 24 hours before serving.
Take out of freezer 3 hours before ready to serve.
It will be slush.
Put in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Yields 100 punch cups full (about 50 people).
For large gatherings, increase as needed.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cake mix, butter, milk and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed.
Stir in drained and chopped mandarin oranges.
Pour mixture into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
In mixing bowl, mix pudding according to package; add undrained pineapple.
Chill.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread between cooled cake layers and top and sides.
Refrigerate.

title: old settler beans
directions: Mix all these ingredients and bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pat tight in bottom of a spring-form pan and bake 10 minutes.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift dry ingredients together for even distribution.
Uneven distribution of leavening causes yellow or brown flecks.

title: apple cranberry relish
directions: Combine sugar, water and orange rind in medium size saucepan. Bring to boiling.
Lower heat.
Simmer until clear (about 2 minutes).
Add apple to saucepan.
Simmer, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.
Add cranberries, ginger, allspice and cinnamon. Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 7 to 8 minutes or until cranberries are soft.
Stir in raisins.
Transfer relish to bowl. Let cool.
Refrigerate overnight or up to two weeks in glass canning jars.

title: crisp fried shrimp
directions: Shell and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact.
In small bowl, beat eggs, cream and salt until well blended.
Pour into shallow dish or pie plate.
Measure bread crumbs onto wax paper.
Dip shrimp into egg mixture, then bread crumbs, coating well. Refrigerate in single layer on cookie sheet for 1 hour.
Pour oil into a medium size saucepan to a 2-inch depth.
Heat to 350°.
Fry shrimp, a few at a time, about 2 minutes or until golden brown. Remove with slotted spoon to a paper towel to drain.
Keep in 250° oven until all the shrimp are cooked.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oats, whole wheat flour, sugar, salt and margarine. Pour over the boiling water and stir.
Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
When batter is cooled to lukewarm, add yeast.
Stir in the white flour; knead 10 minutes.
Let rise well the first time, then punch down and shape into loaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; take meat off the bone.
Cut into small pieces.
In a baking dish, make a layer of each.
Sprinkle cheese and Pepperidge Farm dressing over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish tea cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks and flour.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip in unbeaten egg whites and roll in the nuts.
Make a dent in center of each and bake 5 minutes in a slow oven.
Press down center again and bake 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Save chicken broth.
Melt margarine in dish.
Mix broth and stuffing mix.
Pour over margarine.
Place chicken on top.
Pour soup over the chicken. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix in with milk and beat again.
Dip bread into this mixture and fry both sides until brown.
Do not burn! Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cover with butter and maple syrup.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together and pour over ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Drain off excess vinegar mixture and toss.

title: "shake & bake" coating for microwave(good for fish)
directions: Blend
together
crumbs
and oil and then add remaining ingredients.
Coat	fish and place on flat dish.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Turn and cook for 2 more minutes.

title: dressing mix
directions: Mix together well and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, beating 1 at a time.
Add other ingredients in order.
Roll on a lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Overcooking will make cookies hard.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put 1/3 of cookies in bottom of flowerpot.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Cream the cream cheese.
Add pudding and Cool Whip.
Blend all ingredients and layer cookies and pudding to the top, ending with cookies on top.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Add flowers or other decorations for all occasions.
Add even gummy worms.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all but corn bread.
Fold in corn bread mix.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: frijoles borachos(drunk bean soup)
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Soak overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Add water to cover beans and cook until tender.
Add the remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
May need more water so that the beans are soupy.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, egg and vanilla.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Dough will be a little stiff. Spread evenly into pan.
Beat the cream cheese, 3 eggs and xxx sugar together.
Pour over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses(look no flour)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
With a wooden spoon, stir peanut butter, sugar and eggs in a medium size bowl, until thoroughly blended.
Dough will be slightly sticky. With sugared hands, roll level measuring tbsp into 1-1/4 inch balls. Place 1-1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until cookies look dry with tops cracked.
Remove from oven and immediately press a chocolate Kiss in center of each cookie.
Cook on cookie sheet 1 to 2 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: cumberland mountain watermelon rind pickles
directions: To prepare watermelon, trim off all of the red and the outer green from the rind.
Keep the rind as thick as possible, but red and green parts must be completely removed.
Cut into small, oblong or square pieces, about 1 x 3/4-inch or 1 x 1-inch. Dissolve 1 tablespoon lime into 1 gallon water and soak rind in this overnight (or about eight hours).
Remove rind from lime water.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon of alum in 1 gallon of water.
Soak rind in alum water for 5 minutes.
Remove from alum water.
Place 1/2 pound of ginger root (and do buy whole root and not broken pieces) into one gallon of water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour rind into ginger water and boil for 30 minutes.
Remove rind from ginger water.
Drain.
Prepare syrup.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine fruit juices, sugar and water in a large punch bowl. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, pour ginger ale down side of bowl; stir gently.
Float iced fruit garland in bowl, if desired.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Serve with cracked ice. Makes about 40 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pasta sauce
directions: Combine crumbled beef and onion in 2-quart casserole.
Cook until meat is no longer pink.
Stir halfway through.
Drain.
Blend in all remaining ingredients.
Cook until bubbly and slightly thickened.

title: shrimp delicious
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add green onion and shrimp, stirring until shrimp turn pink, 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and set aside.
Melt remaining butter in another skillet and cook mushrooms until they give up their liquid.
Continue cooking and stir in flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Add shrimp mixture and stir in sour cream. Heat thoroughly, but do not overcook.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Serve with fresh ground black pepper, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spoon bread
directions: *Egg substitute may be used and low-fat sour cream.

title: banana bran nut bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda together.
Add nut meats.
Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs and bran cereal.
Combine bananas, water and vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and let stand for 30 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cooked chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Cook until thick enough to spread.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; blend eggs into butter mixture, one at a time.
In a separate bowl, sift dry ingredients together. Mix with vanilla; add egg mixture.
Fold in apple.
Put in 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together; chill. Serve with or without bread.

title: cupboard cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato pork chop casserole
directions: In greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer onions and potatoes; salt and pepper. Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and onions. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: german soup balls
directions: Add water to soup meat; season to taste and cook slowly for several hours.
A half hour before serving time, make soup ball as follows:
combine the salt and flour and work in the butter.
Beat eggs and add to flour.
Stir in milk, using only enough to make batter thin enough to drop by spoon.
Drop by spoonfuls into the boiling hot broth and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve in hot soup at once.

title: z meat loaf
directions: Saute onion and butter until tender.
In a bowl, add salt, pepper and egg and mix.
Add beef and mix thoroughly.
Add ketchup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce (you may omit the hot sauce), bread crumbs and onion; mix together.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then broil for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve
jello into
hot water. Add
sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Stir to dissolve and chill until thick.
Add cranberries, oranges, celery and nuts (chopped apples can be added).
Pour all into Pyrex dish.
Cut into squares.

title: gram sommer's soft sugar cookie
directions: Beat together until light and fluffy the sugar, oleo and eggs. Mix dry ingredients in sifter.
Sift into egg mixture, adding alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar or cinnamon sugar. Bake in 375° oven until lightly brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Run peaches through colander; add sugar.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into ice cream freezer.
May substitute fresh strawberries, bananas or blueberries for peaches.

title: creamy skillet cabbage
directions: Put cabbage and vinegar and cook covered for 8 minutes until tender but has little crunch.
Remove from heat.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until soft ball stage.
Stir down and add vanilla, pecans and almonds.
Pour and mix with salted popcorn.
Makes about 12 balls.
This is better to leave out some of the butter if you don't add the nuts.

title: golden party punch
directions: Combine juices in serving bowl.
Add four 6-ounce juice cans of water; mix well.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Peel and chop sweet potato. Boil until soft; drain and mash. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Add Bisquick and sugar to mashed sweet potato.
If this seems dry, add a few drops of milk.
Mix together and drop onto prepared cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: "better for you" cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cake pan with Pam.
Mix cake and other ingredients for two minutes on high speed.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until done.
Cool, remove and frost cake with "light" can frosting.
Very good.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle sugar and salt on onion and cucumber.
Add vinegar. Chill about 4 hours.
Cover tightly.

title: cheese rings(make these for new year's eve!)
directions: Have butter at room temperature and blend with the cheese. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or more.
When ready to bake, pinch off little round balls, pat flat and bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Add nuts and then flour.
Make into 3 rolls and put in refrigerator overnight. Slice and bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread dip on bottom of pie platter. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning. Layer on top of bean dip! Layer chopped onion, cheese, tomatoes and black olives. Cover and chill. Serve with Tostitos or favorite chips.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Best if left in fridge overnight. Serve on cocktail rye bread or crackers. It's dynamite !!!!!

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, sugar, salt, milk and pumpkin pie spice.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.

title: rhubarb cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions and pour into a greased (bottom only) 9 x 13 pan. Put rhubarb on top of batter, then sprinkle sugar on rhubarb. Pour whipping cream (do not whip) over this. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
A custard will form on bottom. Store in the refrigerator.

title: putting on the ritz
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients in medium saucepan until thick.
Then add pecans.
Spread on Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: applesauce nuggets
directions: Cream together the first 2 ingredients. Add the egg, applesauce, nuts and butterscotch pieces.
Sift and add the flour, allspice, cloves, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix together well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meat balls and rice
directions: Brown meat balls.
Put cooked rice and meat balls in a greased baking dish.
Pour the remaining ingredients over the rice and meat balls and cook in a low oven for 20 to 30 minutes (350°).

title: raised biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients, working in shortening with fork. Add all liquids; roll thin.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip each in melted butter; place double decker.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Extra dough may be placed in a greased bowl.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: beet jelly
directions: Mix liquid, juice and Sure-Jell; bring to full boil. Add sugar; bring to rolling boil again for 5 minutes. Remove from stove. Add 3 ounce box Jell-O. Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in long casserole dish. Top with Bisquick. Cut margarine on top of Bisquick.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and cornstarch.
Add hot water.
Cook until clear.
Cool.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook on medium heat in open pan until thickens.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in small amount of oil.
Mix remaining ingredients using juice from Worthington Fri-chik to make 1/2 cup liquid to add.
May layer with Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: red rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in bacon grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cover tightly and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Make vanilla pudding according to the directions on the box. Fold in Cool Whip and pumpkin pie mix.
Chill and serve.

title: kentucky hot brown
directions: You will need a bowl served warm from the oven, for each person.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Put half of the above mixture in a mold and place in refrigerator to congeal.
Spread sour cream on top of congealed salad and then put remainder of jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves about 20.

title: special k bars
directions: Heat Karo syrup in large pot.
Add peanut butter and sugar. Then add cereal.
Put in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chocolate and peanut butter chips, stirring constantly.
Pour over bars. Cut right away.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: shrimp patties
directions: Chop or grind shrimp; mix all ingredients together and let set for about 2 hours. Drop by spoonfuls into heated cooking oil.

title: mother's prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except last two in a large bowl.
Beat on medium speed until blended; do not overbeat.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour cake batter into pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Good served warm with vanilla ice cream.	Mother sometimes put a glaze on the cake while it was hot.
Mix powdered sugar with orange juice.
Glaze cake.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate, place the rolls so that the pan and sides are covered nicely and evenly.
Combine egg, milk, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle half of onion over unbaked crust.
Pour egg mixture into crust.
Sprinkle with bacon and remaining onions.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: strawberry-pineapple punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package directions.
Add pineapple juice to Kool-Aid mixture.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello according to package directions.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Let congeal.
You may substitute cherry or strawberry jello and pie filling for different fruit flavors.

title: cranberry eggnog loaf
directions: In a large bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Blend milk, oil, rum and vanilla into slightly beaten eggs and stir into the dry ingredients, mixing just enough to moisten.
Fold in cranberries and pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes or until golden brown and wood pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove to wire rack.
Cool overnight before slicing. Slices may be toasted.
Good served with cream cheese.

title: jessie's banana bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix.
Add bananas and sour cream; mix.
Add flour and baking soda; mix together.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange nut loaf
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk, orange juice and orange peel.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into cream mixture; then blend in chopped nuts.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Let it stand 20 minutes before baking. Bake for 50 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Bake chicken until almost done in oven.
Cook rice with salt and water on top of stove until almost done.
Season chicken before baking.
When both are almost done, pour rice over chicken and bake for 20 minutes in oven at 375°.

title: hot spicy chili
directions: Brown beef; drain grease.
Add onion and saute.
Next, add chili powder; stir well.
Add picante sauce, ketchup and water. Bring to a boil, then let it simmer 30 minutes on low heat.
You can cover pot, but make sure pot is large enough to hold all ingredients.
Can be served with rice.
Leftover pinto beans are good to add to make hot chili beans.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Wash and boil whole potatoes with skins until tender (as for potato salad).
Cool slightly.
Peel and cut up into small chunks or bite size pieces.
In a 5-quart soup pot, cook onion and celery in 2 tablespoons oleo until tender.
Do not brown.
Add broth, water and pepper.
Bring to boiling; boil about 3 minutes.
Add potatoes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Cut shortening, sugar and salt into flour with pastry blender. Make a hole in dry ingredients.
Add yeast that had been dissolved in one cup warm water with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add egg and beat dough as you add the warm water to make a dough that is easy to work with (knead well).

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat the olive oil in large skillet when hot enough to sizzle a drop of water.
Add chicken pieces and brown slowly, turning once. Remove chicken from skillet and add the sauce mixture.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Be careful not to let sauce simmer hard.

title: lemon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls; roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: nothing bread(kid)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well. Pour into prepared pans and bake about 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown and crumble meat.
Add the soup, onion, green pepper, ketchup and mustard.
Simmer in electric skillet for 1 hour or until onion and green pepper are cooked.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: holiday pie
directions: Combine egg, melted butter and sugar; mix well.
Then add the other ingredients and mix well.
Make two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake in unbaked pie shells for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into casserole.
Add broth or enough to make mixture quite moist.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hours. Serve hot with gravy or plain.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar.
Stir until well blended.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add dry ingredients, nut meats and chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: microwave pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat browning
skillet on High for 4 minutes.
Place 2 to 3 chops
in skillet.	Turn quickly to sear on both sides. Cover and cook on High 3 minutes.
Repeat for remaining chops. Salt and pepper after cooking.
Place remaining ingredients in a 4-cup container.	Cover
and cook on High 5 minutes.
Remove chops from browning
skillet.	Pour
in
hot
rice mixture and place chops on top.
Cover
and
cook
on	High
20 minutes or until rice and chops are done.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda. Combine margarine, sugar and pudding mix in a large bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together melting oleo.
Make into small balls.
Dissolve chocolate morsels and paraffin in top of double boiler; dip coconut balls in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix together
all
ingredients,
except soup, and stuff shells.
Mix 2 cans
of
cream
of	chicken soup with 1 cup of broth from	cooked chicken.
Pour over stuffed shells and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with paprika to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter and both sugars until creamy.
Add eggs.
Mix salt and soda with flour and then into mixture.
Add vanilla and then chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° with cover.
Remove cover last 10 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Keeps well.

title: baked chicken breast supreme
directions: In large bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, garlic salt, pepper, celery salt, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Add chicken, coating each piece well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: grape jello dessert
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until completely dissolved.
Add pineapple and juice and mix well.
Add blueberry pie filling, mix well and put into refrigerator to completely set.
When firm, mix with mixer the cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Spread topping on firm jello and return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash, adding cream cheese.
Beat well, then add sour cream.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to potatoes. Beat until light and fluffy.
Place in greased casserole. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's sugarless, eggless, butterless, milkless cake
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in a 1 cup measuring cup.
Fill rest of cup with boiling water.
Empty this into a bowl containing molasses.
Sift in flour.
Mix well.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in greased pan or iron skillet at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve hot with butter or cold with dried fruit.
Also, good baked in muffin pans.

title: onion-yogurt sauce
directions: Combine onion soup mix, yogurt and cucumber, mixing thoroughly. Cover and chill.
Yields 3 cups.

title: vanilla crispies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: In medium bowl, mix cake and eggs.
Add fruit cocktail (juice and all).
Mix all together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and add brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each. Blend in vanilla and chocolate.
Sift flour; fold in egg whites. Add buttermilk, mixing until smooth.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour, milk and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until tested with toothpick.

title: swiss pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in large baking dish.
Place onion, bell pepper and tomatoes on each pork chop; salt and pepper.
Pour rice over chops; add water and the tomato juice that's left.
Bake in covered dish for 1 hour at 375°.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: camp cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk and bring to a boil. Boil for one minute and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper. Let cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: oriental peas
directions: Prepare peas according to directions.
Drain.
Combine with bean sprouts, chestnuts, mushrooms and soup.
Place in casserole dish that has been sprayed.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Add onions on top for last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugars, corn syrup, salt and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook, without stirring, until a little of mixture dropped into cold water forms a soft ball (236° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and let stand until lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla and pecans and beat with spoon until mixture begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Drop from tablespoonful onto wax paper and spread to form patties about 4-inches in diameter.
Let stand at room temperature until firm.
Then wrap individually in Saran Wrap.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 12 pralines.

title: nighty night cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on foil.
Put in oven, then turn oven off.
(Holly Bird's Aunt Olivia, always said, "nighty night.") Do not open until morning.
Remove in a.m.
Makes 30 to 40 cookies.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off fat.
Add taco mix, corn and tomato sauce.
Cook until boiling and then reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Grease a casserole dish. Pour the ground beef mixture into the casserole dish.
Add corn chips and top with grated cheese.
Cook in oven for 10 minutes at 425°.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat hard until light.
Add banana.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Wash barley and rice well in cold water.
Cover bone and meat with cold water.
Add salt.
Cover, but watch.
Cook on low heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Bone can be split.
Strain into a large kettle. Keep squares of meat separate (removing fat, etc.) to add later to soup.
(Dad likes this meat in soup.
Perhaps you do not.)
Add raw vegetables, rice and barley.
Bring to boiling point.
Stir often and then cook slowly for hours, if you like it cooked long.
If not, cook as desired.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Steam or pan boil either red or regular cabbage leaves.
Stuff with mixture of ground chuck, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Roll up cabbage leaf and secure with toothpick.
Brown in hot grease. After rolls are brown, add to skillet the remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or slide into a 350° oven until cabbage is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Drain peaches.
Heat juice to boiling.
Pour jello into juice and dissolve.
Put in blender and add cream cheese and peaches. Blend together.
Let stand 1 hour then fold in cool whip and mold into glasses.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Saute onion in skillet with salad oil.
Add tomato sauce, steak sauce, brown sugar and salt; stir until blended.
Add pork; simmer about 10 minutes.

title: citrus chutney
directions: Peel oranges, reserving peel.
Section oranges over bowl to catch juices.
Remove and discard white membrane from peel. Finely chop enough peel to make 1/4 cup.

title: semolina supreme
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and make smooth paste.
Add milk and cook 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento and eggs to cooked spaghetti.
Mix all together. Bake in buttered dish 25 minutes at 325°.
If desired, top with 1/4 cup olives for garnish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: Cook diced potatoes in salt water or broth until soft.
Add butter.

title: camp cayuga sauerkraut
directions: Cut bacon up and brown lightly.
Leave grease in pan.
Add flour; stir and add sauerkraut with juice.
Mix all ingredients in pan and cover.
Simmer for about 45 minutes.
I cook this recipe according to taste.
You may want to use a little more or less of brown sugar.
Enjoy.

title: catsup
directions: Whiz first 9 ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Then stir in
parsley
and
dill.
Store
in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender in jackets in salt and water.
Put in refrigerator.
Shred potatoes.
Put in 9 x 12-inch buttered dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Mix some potato chips and 1 1/2 cups grated Velveeta cheese together for a crumb topping. Add last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash and onions until tender.
Drain very well. Combine soup, sour cream, cheese and squash.
Add margarine to stuffing mix.
In a casserole dish, alternate layers of stuffing and squash, beginning and ending with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until heated through.

title: champagne salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in fruit and juice, then the whipped topping.
Pour into 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan or loaf pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into a covered baking dish. Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large dish pan.
Put into containers.
Use 1/4 to 1/3 in each cup and add hot water.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion until lightly browned.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook until tender.
Add evaporated milk, corn, salt, pepper and butter.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, water, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in a large saucepan.
Heat until jelly melts.
Drop uncooked meatballs into sauce and simmer 45 minutes.
Refrigerate until excess grease is removed.
Reheat and serve in chafing dish.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut up beef short ribs. Cut up and add onion, bay leaves, water, salt and pepper; simmer.
Add vegetables, ketchup, chili sauce, celery, potatoes, cabbage and Worcestershire sauce.
Let simmer all day.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix beans with taco seasoning and a little milk.
Spread in pan.
Spread avocado dip and then sour cream.
Sprinkle onion, tomatoes, pepper, then cheese.

title: mock whipped cream
directions: Chill a large bowl and beaters.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in fructose.
In chilled bowl, beat together ice water, nonfat milk and vanilla until very frothy.
Gradually add gelatin mixture and continue beating until quite stiff.
Chill for at least 1 hour before using.
Makes about 4 cups.
Contains 3 calories per tablespoon.
This keeps well in refrigerator for about a day.

title: jewel's sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup melted butter and pecans.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Can use the following vegetables to dip: broccoli, cauliflower, celery, carrots, cucumbers, green peppers and radishes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
After cake is cooled, split layers and put coconut mixture between the layers and on top.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 to 4 days in a covered container before slicing.
This draws the flavor out more.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter just until tender-crisp.
Mix sour cream with the mushroom soup and pour over onions.
Gently fold together.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
In a frying pan, stir Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing mix into a bit of melted butter.
Spoon on top of onion mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: citrus avocado salad
directions: Section grapefruit and slice orange.
Cut slices in half. Slice avocado into long thin slices.
Break lettuce into salad bowl.
Arrange other ingredients on top.
Add French dressing sparingly; toss gently.

title: easter bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Blend together scalded milk, pudding mix, margarine, salt and sugar.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well.
Add yeast and beaten eggs.
Add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a lightly greased bowl and let rise until until double.
Turn on floured board and divide dough in 4 parts.
Divide each part into 3 parts and braid.
Place loaves on greased cookie sheets - two loaves on one sheet.
Makes 4 loaves.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Brush each loaf with mixture of 1 beaten egg and 1 tbsp. water.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: chocolate mexicano
directions: Combine cocoa, brown sugar, water, cinnamon sticks, cloves and a pinch of salt in a pan over medium heat. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add milk to cocoa while whisking constantly.
Keep cocoa just below boiling point. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Strain to remove spices. Beat or blend until foamy. Serve hot!

title: dip for fruit
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients on low speed until well blended.
Add 1/2 container Cool Whip and lemon ice.
Beat on low speed until blended well.
Refrigerate.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Line baking dish with hamburger.
Pour one layer of beans, then layer of rice; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dough ornaments
directions: Knead 8 minutes.
Roll and cut with cookie cutter.
Let dry uncovered.

title: chicken noodles parmesan
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper; add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: In a blender, mix salsa and chili sauce; set aside. Mix ground beef, bread crumbs (pumpernickel), salt, pepper, onion and half of the salsa and chili mix. Wrap in foil and put into pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix and pour into layers (makes 3 layers).
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, or until done.

title: ann's garlic dill pickles
directions: Bring to a boil the vinegar, water and salt.
In jars (size of your choice), put the proper amount of garlic and dill half on bottom and the other half on top of cukes after they are packed (raw).
Pour the boiling hot liquid over the cukes and seal. Place in canning pot.
Fill until water covers the lids; bring to a good boil for about 5 minutes.
Remove and cover with a towel until they have sealed.

title: trash
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate morsels and peanut butter.
Add Crispix and mix well.
Pour into white trash bag with powdered sugar.
Shake easily until covered with powdered sugar.
Can be stored in the bag or airtight container.

title: shrimp fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt 3/4 stick butter. Add whipping cream until heated.
Salt and pepper. Add 1/2 Parmesan into this sauce.

title: beef chausauer
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch strips.
Brown beef and onion in oil; drain.
Combine all other ingredients; add to beef.
Cook on low heat for an hour, or until beef is tender.
Serve with bow tie noodles.
Can serve over noodles or as a casserole by mixing meat and noodles in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fabulous cheese casserole
directions: Prepare the day before needed.
Fit the bread strips in the bottom of a lightly greased casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and 1/3 of green and white onions.
Grate 1/3 of the cheese over the onions, even out and press down.
Repeat this with 2 more layers.
Beat the eggs and add the milk, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Pour this mixture over the cheese layers and refrigerate overnight.
Remove the casserole 2 hours before baking.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake uncovered for 50 minutes. (If recipe is doubled, use only 5 cups milk.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green and gold squash pie
directions: Saute all vegetables and spices in the margarine.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine eggs and cream.
Pour over vegetables. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan or Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until set.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Blend together margarine, egg and applesauce.
Sift together flour, soda, spices, salt and substitute sugar.
Add to egg mixture and beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in dates and nuts. Pour in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut or cashew brittle
directions: Cook in 3-quart saucepan sugar, Karo, water, butter and nuts until it reaches 325°, stirring so that it will not scorch. Remove from heat and stir in 2 teaspoons of soda and vanilla. Pour into a 10 x 15-inch tray while it is still foaming.

title: liptauer cheese
directions: Chop first 10 ingredients in processor, then add sour cream. Decorate serving dish with chopped chives.

title: rollards
directions: Fill meat with rest of ingredients.
Roll up and pin with a toothpick.
Brown in bacon grease.
Bake in 350° oven or microwave 3 to 4 minutes on Roast.
Allow standing time.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Boil shrimp and, when cool, mash with fork.
Mix shrimp with softened cream cheese in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: chipped beef dip with crackers
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix cream cheese and milk together. Chop beef into tiny pieces.
Stir into mixture.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Saute butter, pecans and salt.
Spoon over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with "Keebler" round sesame seed crackers.

title: libby's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onion and pepper in oil, then brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients, stirring to keep from sticking.
Bring to a boil. Reduce to simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Stir often during cooking time.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottoms of two 9x5-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, mix pumpkin, sugar. oil, water and eggs. Beat for 1 min. at medium speed.
Add remaining; blend at low speed until moistened.
Bake for 65-75 min. or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 min. and remove from pan.
Freezes Well.

title: frozen daiquiris
directions: Put ingredients in blender with ice cubes.
Blend until slushy, then freeze.

title: chicken creole
directions: Cover chicken in salty water and soak overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and dry with paper towels.
In quart saucepan, combine tomatoes and spices.
Cook 20 minutes while sauteing other ingredients.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon of flour. Add wine.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix together well in a large bowl. Pour into a prepared 9 x 11 glass baking dish. Bake at 350° until a pick inserted in center comes out clean (about 1 hour).

title: angel food cake(mom's)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Slowly add the sugar, flour, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix in cold water and vanilla. Continue to beat until well blended.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° in angel food pan, that has not been greased or floured, for about 1 hour.
Test for doneness.
Serve with ice cream or fruit sauce. May be iced, if desired.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Put in ice cream mixer. Don't forget your ice and rock salt.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook onion and potatoes together in large pot.
Cook the remaining ingredients together until cheese is melted.
Drain potatoes and onions.
Add rest of ingredients together and simmer together.
Add green onions or chives and bacon bits on top when served if desired.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press out rolls in sheet pan like a pizza pan and bake.
Cool and spread with mixture (first 3 ingredients, creamed). Refrigerate overnight at least.
Before serving, top with veggies (celery, broccoli, Cheddar cheese, carrots, radishes and diced meat).

title: fran's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix: sugar, milk, salt and cocoa.
Boil to 232°.
Add: 1/2 stick butter, peanut butter, and vanilla.
Stir well.
Spread fudge into a buttered dish.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups milk with Dream Whip; beat until fluffy.
Then add other milk with pudding mix; mix until thick.
Add coconut. Mix by hand.
Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Toast some coconut to put on top.
Delicious, but fattening.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Boil eggplant until tender, then drain. Make a batter with all other ingredients. Add the eggplant to the batter and blend well with electric mixer. Drop by spoonfuls in a little hot oil and fry until golden brown on each side. Drain on paper towels. This makes about a dozen fritters.

title: mashed potatoes with carrots and onions
directions: Saute onion in the butter (or oil) until brown.
Cook potato and carrot in boiling water until tender.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into a casserole.
Top with mixture of cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 3-step biscuits
directions: Stir together all ingredients. (Dough will be crumbly.) Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 3 or 4 times. Pat or roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cutter and place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden. Yield: 8 biscuits.

title: salsa de barbacoa(barbecue sauce)
directions: Cook onions and garlic in fat until tender; add remaining ingredients and boil for 5 minutes or until thick.
Pour over broiled or roasted meat, or use as sauce for reheating cold meat. Serve very hot.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: Combine bananas, oats, milk and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with banana mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Cook broccoli for 7 minutes.
Put broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix both soups and milk and heat until blended.
Cook rice as directed on box.
Pour rice and soup mixture into pan.
Salt and pepper each piece of chicken and lay over top.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Add first 4 ingredients together for filling, set aside.
Mix last 3 ingredients together.
Take 1/4 of soup mixture add it to the chicken mixture.
Place approx. 1/2 cup chicken mixture on a flour tortilla and roll up.
Place 8-10 in a 13x9-inch pan.
Pour remaining soup mixture over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: susu's corn bread
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in iron skillet.
Pour into above mixture; cook in iron skillet at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix
ingredients,
except for paprika and chili powder. Refrigerate for
1	hour.
Divide and make 2 rolls.
Roll each roll in paprika and chili powder.

title: best holiday dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix the eggs, salt, 1/3 cup sugar and butter. Meanwhile, proof the yeast. Dissolve in warm water (100° to 110°) with 1 teaspoon sugar. When yeast mixture is frothy and bubbly, add to egg-sugar mixture. Add flour slowly using a hand mixer or big spoon. Dough will be very soft. Cover with cloth and let rise 4 hours at room temperature. Gently punch down; cover with bowl lid and refrigerate overnight. About 4 hours before baking, take the dough out of fridge and shape as desired. Spray pan with Pam and place rolls so that they touch. Allow to rise 3 1/2 to 4 hours at room temperature. Bake at 400° approximately 10 to 12 minutes until lightly golden brown. Yield: 5 to 6 dozen rolls.

title: "3 minute" chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter, vanilla and cocoa together.
Put on stove on medium high.
Do not stir while cooking.
When mixture first comes to boil, time 3 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter and 3/4 jar of marshmallow cream.
Beat quickly with mixer on low.
Pour immediately into greased 13 x 11-inch pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 2 loaves.
Grease and flour pans good.

title: buttermilk delight
directions: Cook jello and pineapple to full boil; stir occasionally. Cool to room temperature.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix until Cool Whip is melted.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/2 cups flour, salt, sugar and undissolved yeast. Set aside. Combine milk, water and margarine in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine does not need to melt.

Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add 1/2 cup flour. Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in enough flour to make soft dough. Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and place in warm place (or set bowl in pan of water at about 100°) for 15 minutes.
Turn dough out onto floured board.
Shape rolls. Cover and let rise in a warm place free from draft for about 15 minutes. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sad cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until cake falls!

title: caesar salad(foolproof)
directions: Salt bowl.
Completely mash the garlic in the bowl.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, egg and pepper and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add vinegar, oil and lemon juice.
Stir.
Add Parmesan cheese and mix well.
Add pepper to taste.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind fruit together and drain 15 minutes.
Mash all lumps out of turmeric and mustard.
Add this and other seasoning to vinegar and sugar and boil hard for 15 minutes or until sugar dissolves. Add well drained fruit and boil for 5 minutes, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Put into prepared jars and seal.
Process 10 minutes at simmering temperature.

title: melt in your mouth muffins
directions: Combine egg and milk.
Add to mix.
Batter will be lumpy. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full or fill 1/2 full.
Make hole in center.
Add 1/2 teaspoon jam or jelly and top with more mix to fill cups.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grandma's coconut pie
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients on stove in thick pan or double boiler.
Make thickening with cornstarch and milk.
Add to boiling mixture.
Cook until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Add coconut.

title: oven pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in a little oil and season with salt and pepper.
Place drained pork chops in a shallow baking dish.
In a saucepan, combine soup, catsup, Worcestershire and onion.
Heat just enough to mix together.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover the last 15 minutes.

title: frozen pineapple delight salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Pour into muffin tins lined with paper cups.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 10.

title: blue ribbon brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Combine cocoa and soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water and stir well.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: our sand tarts
directions: Combine flour and pecans.
Set aside.
Mix butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla; now add flour/pecan mixture.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface.
Either cut in strips or use biscuit cutter to make round ones.
Bake at 425° on greased cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
While still warm, sprinkle with sugar.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator.
(Can be frozen.)

title: corn dip
directions: Mix all ingredients
in order given and chill over night. Enjoy!

title: western skillet rice
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat, stirring frequently.
Stir in the onion soup mix, water, rice and tomatoes; simmer, covered, for 25 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Top with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: toasted butter pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Toast pecans in 2 sticks of margarine. Prepare cake mix as directed, adding 1 stick of margarine and 1/2 of the pecans.
Bake in 8-inch round cake pans.
Let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Tear dried beef into small pieces.
Divide in half.
Mix one-half with cream cheese and dry dressing mix.
Shape into ball. Roll in remaining dried beef.

title: easy chicken dinner
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, place chicken.
Cover with vegies.
Pour dressing over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Easy, low-fat and delicious!

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix buttermilk and oatmeal together and let sit 8 to 10 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients except butter.
Mix all together and add 2 tablespoons butter. Cook.

title: tuna fish open-faced sandwiches
directions: Put on open-faced bun or bread and brown in toaster oven or regular oven.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter paisley brownies
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter in large mixer bowl.
Add sugar and brown sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to peanut butter mixture.

title: crab newburg
directions: Melt butter.
Slowly blend in flour over low heat 3 to 4 minutes to cook flour.
Gradually add hot milk, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add seasonings and crab meat.
Blend.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: layered casserole
directions: Brown meat with spices.
Drain grease from meat.
Layer all ingredients in deep dish as follows: meat, beans, potatoes, onions, cheese and soup on top.
Cover dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Form into two balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill.
Set out to soften before serving with crackers.

title: mushroom and rice side dish
directions: Saute onion and butter until brown.
In a casserole bowl, mix rice, soup, water, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Bake at 300° uncovered about 1 hour or until rice is cooked.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg; cut in shortening. In a bowl, beat eggs; add sugar, sweet milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Roll out to desired thickness; sprinkle with additional sugar.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake about 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Yield:
30 cookies.

title: marinated green beans
directions: (1 10-ounce package of frozen whole beans may be substituted for fresh.)

title: hot crab dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, white wine and milk; add garlic salt (to taste), mustard, sugar, onion juice and Lawry's.
Fold in crab meat.
Heat in double boiler.
Serve in chafing dish with Triscuits.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt cheese in a double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir. Keep in hot chafing dish.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Combine sweet potato, brown sugar and butter flavor Crisco.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until well blended and fluffy.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Stir buttermilk and sweet potato mixture alternately into dry ingredients.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch round cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 biscuits.

title: grandma briden's black and white pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Scald cream in a heavy saucepan.
Beat egg yolks with 6 tablespoons sugar and salt. Slowly add cream, stirring constantly.
Return mixture to the pan and cook over low heat about 5 minutes until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in softened gelatin.
Pour into a bowl and chill until it mounds with a spoon.
Beat egg whites until frothy. Add 1/4 cup sugar gradually, beating until stiff.
Fold into chilled custard.
Divide mixture in half.
Add almond flavoring to one half; blend well and pour into pie shell.
To remaining half, add melted chocolate and vanilla flavoring.
Pour over first layer.
Chill.
Just before serving, arrange banana slices in a circle on top of the pie.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine corn, candy and nuts.
Melt marshmallows and margarine.
Pour over corn mixture and press into tube pan or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: mrs. sweatt's pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, oleo and sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix other dry ingredients together and add small portions at a time, beating well along with the sour cream and flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for one hour or until toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean.

title: m&m oatmeal cookie bars
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and fruit cocktail. Save juice from pineapple. Mix all other ingredients, except pudding.
Stir well; place in a bowl.
Mix dry pudding with pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit. Chill before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pie filling and pineapple with juice.
Mix together well.
Chill.

title: banana zucchini bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients and set aside.
Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl; beat well.
Stir in bananas and zucchini.
Add flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pans.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery in butter until soft and tender.
Add soups, parsley, onion tops, shrimp and pimento.
Stir and heat until hot.
Stir in rice and pour into a 3-quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Chop cherries. Mix all ingredients in order listed. Add cherries. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. It is wonderful with cream cheese spread on.

title: rainbow crayons
directions: Remove paper wrappers from lots of brightly colored broken pieces of crayons.
Line each cup of a muffin tin with a piece of foil. Fill each cup halfway with contrasting crayon pieces.
Bake crayons in preheated 300° oven for 5 to 7 minutes. Watch closely because crayons melt quickly.
Melt just enough to blend the colors.
Carefully remove tin from oven and let crayons cool approximately 30 minutes.
When cool, remove from tin and peel off foil.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all this and put in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed potato chips. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: easy mini cheese cakes
directions: You will need 2 1/2 to 3 dozen small baking cups.

title: easy turkey and stuffing
directions: Make Stove top stuffing according to directions. On bottom of 9x13 pan, layer
stuffing and green beans.
Add cut up slices of turkey and mix together. Add chicken broth and bake in oven at 350° for 45 mins. to 1 hour.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Serve with fresh vegetables or chips.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix well and bake 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with a fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cut up veggies.
Mix all together; refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Cook rice.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pie pan.
Mix rice, 2 tablespoons cheese and one egg.
Press mixture over bottom and sides of pie pan.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: german chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in saucepan on low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, butter and remaining evaporated milk.
Press 1/2 of this mixture onto bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle baked crust with chocolate and nuts.
Then top with caramel mixture; spoon the remaining cake mixture over top. Return to 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until set.
Remove from oven to cool.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 2 cups.
Prep time:
15 minutes, plus refrigerating.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: In large pan, dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add carrots, celery and potatoes.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and cook until tender.
Add soup and cheese; cook until melted.

title: cut out sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, vanilla and sour cream. Blend well.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Add slowly to the creamed mixture.
Mix well. Divide into 4 to 5 balls and chill overnight or 3 to 4 hours. Roll on a floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes and sprinkle with colored sugar crystals, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and flavoring.
Fold in flour. Drop from teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Makes approximately 60 cookies.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute rice in three tablespoons of butter.
Mix all ingredients together except broccoli.
Butter a baking dish.
Cook frozen broccoli as directed on package.
Mix rice and broccoli and pour heated sauce over it.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell. Melt chocolate and pour into bottom of pie shell evenly.
Wash and cut strawberries, leaving a flat surface. Place strawberries, pointed end up, evenly across entire chocolate surface.
Melt jelly and brush to glaze strawberries. Refrigerate.
Let pie stand at room temperature 1 hour before serving to allow chocolate to soften.

title: chinese barbecued baby drumsticks
directions: Marinate the wings in ingredients, well mixed, for 2 hours or longer, turning so each piece is well covered.
Cover with foil and refrigerate.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, in a shallow pan for an hour or longer.
Turn and baste 2 or 3 times with the marinade.
A small amount of marinade in the baking pan will make a thicker glaze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone; cut in bite-size pieces. Set aside.
In saucepan, put peas, onion, soup and milk.
Add chicken to this mixture and heat.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing mix until it is moist.
Cover bottom of 2-quart casserole baking dish with stuffing; leave a small amount for top of casserole.
Pour in hot chicken mixture and thickened broth. Cover top with remaining stuffing.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.
This is an excellent way to also use leftover turkey.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cook noodles & drain then add to bottom of 9 x 13 pan (add a little sauce with noodles). Brown ground beef, drain. Add sauce to mix well. Start layering ingredients by sprinkling mozzarella to noodles. Add cottage cheese. Put meat sauce next. Sprinkle mozzarella all over top. Then sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Put in oven for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread.
Let cool.
Cook bacon crisp.
Let cool.
Chop rest of ingredients.
Crumble cornbread and mix all together.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix together.
Set aside. Spread beans on flat surface.
Cover bottom completely.
Spread sour cream mixture over bean layer.
Cover with grated cheese, diced tomatoes, scallions and whatever else catches your fancy.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well. Make 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Yields 42 cookies. Great for diabetics.

title: vanilla ricotta creme
directions: Mix together in a dessert bowl. Serve chilled.

title: tomato wine
directions: Mix all together in a crock.
Mix for 10 days.
Squeeze all out and put through a colander or cloth.
I let it hang and drip overnight, then it settles overnight.
Siphon into bottles and dip in wax.

title: sausage bread
directions: Half the thawed bread dough and roll out to size of bread pan. Brown sausage; season with salt, pepper and garlic.
Drain fat. Stir in beaten egg, broccoli (well drained), Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Spread on the rolled out dough and roll up like jellyroll cake.
Seal ends with leftover dough.
Grease pan lightly.
Place roll in pan and cover lightly with cooking oil. Bake at 350° until brown and crusty, about 45 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: chicken florentine(good covered dish)
directions: Cool chicken and remove skin and rib cage.
Place spinach in 9 x 13-inch ungreased casserole.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and seasonings together and spread over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese and buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° uncovered 40 to 50 minutes.
May be assembled day ahead, except for crumbs.

title: salsa
directions: Scald, peel, chop and chunk tomatoes.
Chop onions in medium sized pieces.
Chop peppers.
(The more seeds you use, the hotter the salsa.)
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, garlic salt, chili powder, black powder and cumin.
Mix all together and bring to a boil. Simmer on medium heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir often.
Place in clean hot canning jars and hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and put in long pan. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Heat peas and mash.
Add all other ingredients and mix. Serve.

title: nacho popcorn
directions: Pop the corn.
Melt margarine.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour over popped corn, toss and enjoy!

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and sugar in oblong pan.

title: cold oven lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, salt, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add flavoring, flour and milk alternately. Add baking powder and 1 cup flour.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls and put in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: washington fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roasted sweet and white potatoes
directions: Put butter, oil, potatoes, onion and garlic in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 475° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done. Stir every 10 minutes.

title: busy-day fruit salad
directions: Combine orange sections and pineapple chunks; place in lettuce-lined bowl.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Serve with mayonnaise blended with pineapple syrup.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken divon
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes, drain.
Layer broccoli and chicken in 8 inch square baking dish.
Blend soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Layer cheese & mixture of cracker crumbs and margarine over top.
Bake at 350° fro 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and water in 2-quart baking dish; add in chicken and top off with bacon.
Place in oven at 400° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly; place in a loaf pan.
Bake 90 minutes or until done.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well.
Pour in uncooked pie shell. When half done, sprinkle top with Grape-Nuts.
Baking time is 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in dish.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, vegetable oil and flour.
Beat for 20 strokes and let rest for 5 minutes.
Put in pan that is oiled.
I use my largest cookie sheet and spread dough thin.

title: mexican baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: penuche fudge
directions: Lightly butter a 9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Line with foil.
Lightly grease foil with butter.
In heavy 3-quart saucepan mix brown sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Set aside without stirring.
Cool to lukewarm.
With wooden spoon, beat until thick and creamy.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Quickly turn into greased loaf pan.
Cool completely and refrigerate.
Turn out of pan in 1 block.
Discard foil and cut into pieces.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet with onion and pepper.
Drain grease. In a boiler, mix all ingredients together.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Serve with saltine crackers.

title: crispy corn dogs
directions: Combine flour, corn meal, sugar, mustard, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, egg and shortening.
Mix until smooth.
Pour mixture into a tall glass and dip hot dogs in one at a time.
Fry in vegetable oil heated to 375° until golden brown.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 4 tablespoons of oleo.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Separate rolls into 8 rectangles.
Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mix into each rectangle. Pull 4 corners to top center and twist.
Press to seal.
Place on cookie sheet and brush with oleo.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together in a large mixing bowl and cover; refrigerate. Mix every day for 6 days.
