Form into sausage-type rolls and bake on a broiling pan for 3 1/2 hours at 180°.

title: fruity bread pudding
directions: Melt
butter and combine with beaten eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla,
milk,
fruit
and seasonings.
Pour over bread cubes (if needed, add 1/2 cup more bread crumbs or cubes).
Dot with butter. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until light brown on top.
May be served with whipped cream or cooked lemon sauce.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Mix in some of the flour and then some of the milk, alternating until all of each is incorporated.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Put in cold oven and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cabbage relish
directions: Mix the vegetables and sprinkle with the salt.
Add the water and let the vegetables soak in the brine for 1 hour.
Drain. Rinse in clear cold water and drain again.
Add the vinegar, sugar and seeds. Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack boiling hot into hot jars and seal.

title: salsa
directions: Add chopped firm tomatoes, chopped green onions, chopped fresh cilantro and garlic powder to taste.
Add the picante sauce.
Mix together; dip with chips.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: To make sauce, heat water and dissolve bouillon cubes.
Add all spices and sauces.
Slice chicken breasts into 1/2-inch strips. Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-sizes.
Heat oil in wok.
Add chicken.
Stir and cook until golden brown.
Add onions and stir.
Add carrots, broccoli and cauliflower.
Stir until they start to soften.
Add mushrooms.
Add sauce when vegetables start to stick.
Combine cornstarch and milk and stir into sauce to thicken.
Cover and let steam.
Add tomatoes before serving. Cook briefly.
Serve over rice.

title: quick chicken noodle soup
directions: Prepare broth as directed on can, using a 3-quart saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Stir in noodles, chicken and vegetables.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
You can also add a can of cream of chicken soup.
Serve with crackers.

title: country breakfast
directions: Cook 6 slices of bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet and pour off excess fat.
Add 4 cups cooked cubed potatoes, 1/2 cup chopped green pepper and 2 tablespoons onions.
Cook until browned.
Season with salt and pepper.
Break 6 eggs over potatoes and cook until eggs are done.
Sprinkle with 4 ounces of cheese and crisp bacon.
Cover until cheese melts.

title: dill-sweet pickles
directions: Wash dills well in cold water and drain.
Mix in large container with sugar and vinegar.
Refrigerate for several days; stir at least once daily.
Surprisingly good!

title: homemade dressing
directions: Cook celery, onion, chicken and turkey broth until celery and onion are tender.
May have to add more broth.
Put all crumbs and seasonings in large bowl.
Add eggs; stir in broth and mix with hands until moist.
Add sage to taste.
Place around turkey; uncover and brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Put into a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle potato chips over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top and heat until melted.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Arrange eggplant slices in single layer on cookie sheet; broil 4 inches from heat 5 minutes on each side or until lightly browned.

title: oatmeal drops
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
When batter is smooth, stir in next 3 ingredients.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen drops.

title: flamboyant rice
directions: Heat all ingredients in a large saucepan to boiling; stir once or twice.
Reduce to simmer, cover tightly and cook until rice is tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Do not uncover during this time. Remove pan from heat and remove bay leaf.
Fluff with a fork. Cover and let stand for 5 more minutes.

title: deviled ham and cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the nuts.
Chill.
Form in shape and garnish with nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan icebox cookies
directions: Mix by hand in large bowl.
Cream shortening and add brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar together.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix in nuts.
Turn out on wax paper and form into rolls 2-inches in diameter.
Roll in wax paper and store in refrigerator overnight or until firm.
Slice and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Let cookies fall after out of oven.

title: creamy cheesecake squares
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and flour together in a large bowl. Stir in the butter and mix with your hands until crumbly.
Remove one cup of the mixture to be used later as a topping.
Place remainder in an 8-inch square pan and press firmly.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets mozzarella
directions: Cut chicken breasts in halves.
Cut off fat.
Pound.
I use a rolling pin.
Lay Mozzarella cheese on cutlet.
Roll up and serve with toothpicks.
Dip in egg, then bread crumbs.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook on foiled pan.
Easy clean up.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Place the flour, baking powder and salt in a medium-size bowl; make a well in the center and pour in the milk or water.
Stir briskly (just until dry ingredients are uniformly moistened).

title: low-fat pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray a jellyroll pan. Combine egg whites, sugar, buttermilk, corn syrup, oil and pumpkin in a large mixing bowl.
Combine flour, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon and baking soda in a medium bowl.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture; stir until just combined.
Add raisins, if using.

title: festive honey-pecan chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken evenly with flour, coating both sides.
Dip each breast into beaten egg, then into bread crumbs, coating both sides and pressing to adhere.
In a skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat.
Add half of the chicken and cook, turning once until lightly browned, 3 to 4 minutes each side.
Remove chicken to serving platter and keep warm.
Repeat with remaining oil and chicken.

title: baked bread pudding
directions: Chop
biscuits
or
stale bread fine.
Pour enough milk over this
to
cover nicely.
Add 2 beaten eggs.
Flavor with nutmeg. Put in pudding pan or bread pan and bake in 375° oven until thick. Serve with sauce.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Whisk egg; mix wet ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add together; whisk until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Cook on hot griddle.
Pancakes will also be thin.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and cream cheese.
Add vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add eggs and flour.
Grease Bundt pan. Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before turning out.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in spaghetti, chicken and parsley.
Heat through, stirring often. Can be served directly from pan or poured into a casserole dish for more attractive serving at the table.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup and sour cream.
Set aside half of mixture to use later.
Also save back at least half of diced green onion and shredded cheese.
(I like to use Longhorn or sharp Cheddar.) Combine remaining ingredients except tortillas.
Put the mixture in each tortilla and roll together as burro.
Spread a small amount of soup/cream mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.
Line filled tortillas in a row.
Makes about 12.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Mix flour with mixture.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Add chopped nuts.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and then add onions, mushrooms, water, bouillon and noodles.
Heat the mixture to a boil, then turn to medium-low and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in the sour cream; heat through and then serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Thoroughly mix first 8 ingredients.
Then add applesauce and baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: frankenmuth bean salad
directions: Mix everything together and refrigerate 24 hours.
The longer it sets, the better it gets.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour well.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from eye and add margarine, vanilla and coconut. Pour into prebaked pie shell.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Frost cold cake.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Broil ribs until brown.
Cut ribs into serving size pieces and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in slow cooker and top with other ingredients.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: You will need 1 huge deep fryer and hypodermic needle.

title: chili wraps
directions: Saute onion in oil in a large skillet.
Add the ground beef. Brown and break up.
Season with black, white and red pepper, hot sauce, chili powder, oregano, ketchup and garlic powder.
Place 1/8 of meat mixture down center of softened tortilla (see Tip). Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Fold over top bottom edges.
Fold one side over filling, then other side.
Secure with toothpicks. Heat oil, 1/2-inch high, in a heavy skillet.
Fry tortillas folded side down first.
Turn, brown other side.
Drain.
Serve hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts. Mix well and form into a ball. Roll in pecans. Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: tomato pudding(yields 6 servings)
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add brown sugar, stirring constantly, cooking until sugar is melted.
Combine tomatoes, half and half and the vegetable/seasoning packet.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Add stuffing crumbs, stirring until moistened. Stir in eggs.
Spread into a greased two-quart casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until set.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruits into 4-cup glass measure.
Set aside juices. Place plum in center of shallow 1 1/2-quart glass serving dish. Arrange peaches, pineapple and banana around plums.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Blend cornstarch into fruit juices.
Stir in honey and lemon juice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, and water until slightly thickened. Remove from heat and add the box of strawberry jello.
Set until lukewarm, then pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Top with Dream Whip.

title: sauteed peppers with balsamic vinegar
directions: Core, remove seeds and thinly slice peppers.
In a large skillet, heat oil over medium-low heat.
Add peppers.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add the sugar, salt and vinegar and stir well.
Simmer until most of the liquid has evaporated, about 5 minutes more.
Serve hot, warm or at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: rich chocolate shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: tangy flank steak
directions: Place steak in a large, shallow container.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well; pour over steak.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours, turning steak frequently.
Can marinate longer.

title: italian ziti bake
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
In large saucepan over medium-low heat, warm vegetable oil.
Add onion, zucchini and garlic.
Cover pan and cook until vegetables
are very soft, about 10 minutes.
Stir in crushed tomatoes, oregano,
basil and red pepper flakes.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: milk pie
directions: Melt butter; mix sugar and cornstarch.
Mix with butter.
Add milk and stir well.
Cook in microwave for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 5 minutes longer or until thick.
Put in baked crust. Sprinkle top very lightly with nutmeg.
Let cool before serving.

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Fold in other ingredients. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
If cake is browning too fast during the last 30 minutes, put a piece of aluminum foil over the top.

title: banana split cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 1/3 cup sugar. Mix well and press into bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish or pan. Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla until blended. Add eggs and pineapple juice; mix until fluffy. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until center is almost set. Cool and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight (overnight is better). Remove from refrigerator and spread pineapple over cheesecake. Slice bananas over pineapple and spread Cool Whip over top. Drizzle chocolate syrup over toppings and add walnuts on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; combine with sugar. Let stand for 2 hours. Combine remaining ingredients and fold in whipped cream. Chill well.

title: baked corn
directions: Grease small pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Blend
and pour into pan.
Bake 15 -20 mins. at 350° then reduce heat to 325° for 1 hour.
Test with knife to come out clean. Serves 4.

title: eyes of texas
directions: Saute meat, onion and garlic; stir in remaining ingredients except chips and cheese.
Alternate layer of meat mixture and chips, beginning and ending with meat mixture.
Put in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes well.
Serves 8.
(We use this on New Years Day.)

title: pecan pralines
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar.
Add to warm milk, a little at a time.
Add remaining sugar.
Cook to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Beat.
Drop on waxed paper or buttered surface.
Yields 35 pralines.

title: cherry tart
directions: Pour the can of pie filling in bottom of 10 inch pie plate or 9 x 9 inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Pour melted butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top is browned.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion; cook about 10 minutes. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly, about 2 minutes.
Gradually add broth and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil, stirring until it has thickened.
Add broccoli.
Cover and simmer until broccoli is tender.
Add milk and stir; simmer until ready to eat.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: magical biscuits
directions: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees.
Mix the flour, baking powder and salt in a medium mixing bowl.
Shake the whipping cream vigorously.
Add to the flour mixture, stirring until a soft dough forms.
Pat the dough 1/2-inch thick on a lightly floured surface. Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Arrange 1-inch apart on a lightly greased 11 x 17-inch baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 biscuits.

title: apple dump cake(simple and delicious)
directions: Mix well in a bowl.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: russian tea(serves 6)
directions: Brew tea in water for about 5 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring almost to a boil and then let simmer about 15 minutes.
Preparation time:
30 minutes.

title: cheesy italian bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pasta, meat, soup and spaghetti sauce.
Add pepper, seasoning and 2 cups of cheese.
Mix and place in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 25 minutes.

title: carrot coconut cake
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Beat oil, sugar and eggs until well blended. Add flour mixture and beat until smooth. Stir in pineapple, carrots and coconut. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: chicken risotto
directions: Combine rice, celery, peas, 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt in medium saucepan; heat to bubbling.
Cover and simmer 12 minutes or until water is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: whipped cream dressing
directions: Heat all ingredients, except whipping cream, just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Beat whipping cream in cold 1 1/2-quart bowl until stiff.
Fold in egg mixture.
This is the best over any fruit salad.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a casserole or baking pan, put a layer of sliced zucchini, salt and pepper to taste.
Add a layer of chopped onions, a layer of browned hamburger or sausage, then add a layer of bread crumbs, partially cooked rice or macaroni.
Add a layer of cheese.
Repeat the layers as desired, until pan or dish is full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until zucchini is tender.
Add last layer of cheese 10 minutes before it is done.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Beat each ingredient in order.
Pour in unbaked pie crust. (Makes 2 pies.)
Bake at 325 for 1 hour.

title: grape ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and put in freezer can.
Fill up freezer can with homogenized milk (about 1 quart).
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave then mix in other ingredients until well blended and form into a ball and sprinkle with paprika or parsley flakes.
Garnish with fresh parsley.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans as directed on package, drain.
Melt butter, add flour.
Cook gently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, onion, mustard and sour cream.
Fold in beans.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dutch chocolate bars
directions: Early in day, preheat oven to 350°.
Into small bowl, measure oats, brown sugar, walnuts, 1/3 cup flour, 4 tablespoons margarine (1/2 stick, melted), 1/4 teaspoon baking soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well mixed. Pat mixture into bottom of floured 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Bake 10 minutes.

title: grandma's brown sugar pie
directions: Add in order given; pour in unbaked pie shells (deep-dish crusts better). Bake at 400° about 50 minutes, until done.

title: swiss chicken(serves 8)
directions: Place chicken breasts in buttered baking dish.
Cover each breast with one slice of cheese.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter over low heat.
Add flour and blend over heat until smooth and bubbling.
Slowly stir in milk and chicken broth.
Season with salt and pepper to taste; add wine.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Spread over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on thickness of breasts.
Good with sauteed mushrooms in the sauce.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add 3 or more tablespoons water if batter is dry.
Add vanilla and apples.
Bake, cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into casserole. Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Let stand before serving.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash and dry with paper towel the chicken pieces.
Then rub with light coat of cooking oil and roll in crushed potato chips.

title: moussaka
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add cinnamon.
Dilute tomato paste with 2 cans of water and add to mixture.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Rinse and drain eggplant. Simmer in boiling water for 10 minutes; drain.
Arrange eggplant slices in shallow casserole dish.
Add meat sauce.
Cover with grated cheese.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and place in oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Layer chicken over the top.
Pour the sauce (recipe follows) over the chicken. Sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake in a slow oven at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice pilaf and pickled fruit.

title: german butter balls
directions: Shape with palms into balls using 1 teaspoon per cookie. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°. When baked and practically cooled, roll in 10x sugar one at a time for dusting.
Yield:

title: cheese pudding
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Dip bread, both sides, cube and alternate in greased casserole with cheese. Beat egg yolks with other ingredients, pour over casserole. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites (awkward, but essential). Refrigerate 24 hours. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: ice cream sundae pie
directions: Allow ice cream to soften slightly.
Spoon into crust.
Cover and freeze until firm (about 3 hours).
Serve pie wedges with chocolate topping, whipped cream, nuts and a cherry.

title: dietetic applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 items.
Sift together the next 7 ingredients.
Add the oats, raisins and nuts.
Beat well into the applesauce mixture and spread in greased 9 x 9-inch cake pan or drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix the cranberries and the sugar.
Set
aside	for one hour. Add the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate
overnight or freeze to serve.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix dry milk with warm water.
Heat in double boiler until thoroughly dissolved.
Add sugar and continue to heat and stir until sugar is completely dissolved.
Cool and use as you would Eagle Brand condensed milk.

title: chicken monroe
directions: Pound cutlets thin.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread them with 1/4 cup butter.
Blend remaining butter with herbs.
Set aside.
Cut cheese into 8 sticks; place 1 in center of each cutlet and roll, tucking in ends to seal.
Roll breasts in flour; dip in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Arrange in a well-buttered baking dish.
Pour remaining butter mixture on chicken.
(Recipe may be done ahead to this point and refrigerated, if desired.)

title: chili dip
directions: Layer ingredients in a pie plate or shallow dish, starting with cream cheese, then chili, taco hot sauce and ending with cheese.
Microwave for about 4 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tandy cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add sugar.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add mixture alternately with milk.
Add butter. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Remove from oven.
Spread with peanut butter while cake is warm.
Refrigerate.
Then cover with melted chocolate bars or your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: sunday dinner roast beef
directions: Season
roast
with
salt
and pepper.
Preheat oven to 500° until
light
goes off.
Bake roast 8 minutes per pound. Turn oven
off
and
do not open door until cool, about 2 1/2 hours. Slice; arrange on platter, garnished with parsley.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing mix as directed on box, except increase butter to 1/2 cup.
Place zucchini and onion in boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix zucchini in bowl with sour cream and cream of chicken soup.

title: crunchy bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix dressing and sugar in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate several hours.

title: katrina's peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add at low speed.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, or until set.
Cool 2 minutes.
Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: caramel apple crisp
directions: Mix vanilla wafers crumbs, walnuts, oats, cinnamon and salt in a bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of the mixture into an 8-inch glass dish.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Toss apples with lemon juice in bowl.
Spread over crust.
Drizzle with caramel topping.
Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture. Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until apples are tender. Turn dish 1/2 turn after 2 1/2 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: chili dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order given on serving dish.
Microwave to melt cheese.
Serve with Fritos or nacho chips.

title: oven fries
directions: Slice potatoes to desired shape and pat dry.
Lightly coat slices with oil and arrange on a cookie sheet.
Roast in a hot oven until tender and brown.
Serve with Scrambled Onions.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil sugar, water and coffee.
Cool.
Add vodka and vanilla beans.
Pour into 2 1/2 gallon bottles.
Turn upside-down for one week.
Reverse for one week, then upside-down again.
Finished at the end of third week.

title: chicken strata(main dish)
directions: Butter 2 slices bread and cut into
1/2 inch cubes; set aside. Cut remaining 6 slices into 1
inch cubes.
Place half of unbuttered cubes in bottom of 2
quart casserole dish.
Mix together mayonnaise, soup, salt, pepper,
chicken
and vegetables. Pour
over
bread
cubes	in
dish.
Place
remaining unbuttered cubes over top.	Combine milk
and eggs;
pour over bread and chicken mixture.	Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 hour or overnight.	Place buttered bread
cubes over top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Place shredded
cheese
over top and return to oven until cheese is well melted.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix butter and eggs.
Add sugar, spices, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add berries, two cups of flour, milk and remainder of flour.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease or line muffin tins with paper. Measure 1st seven ingredients into large bowl.
In small bowl, mix eggs, zucchini and oil.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture all at once, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin tins.
Bake for 25 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Makes 12 (3-inch) muffins or about 18 (2 1/2-inch) muffins.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the above ingredients together and roll into balls.
If dough seems too stiff, add a few drops of milk until you have desired consistency.
You will need to use your hands.
Place balls on waxed paper lined cookie sheets and freeze at least 24 hours before dipping.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll
into
balls the size of a walnut.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes until edges are lightly browned.

title: cheese pie
directions: Line a pie pan with pastry (one 10-inch or two 8-inch).
Beat eggs and sugar.
Continue beating until light.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well and strain.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, until center is firm.
Turn off oven, open door and let stand in oven for 60 minutes.
Cool.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef, then add onion and celery and saute 5 minutes. Add all but cabbage and bring to a boil. Turn heat to low and cook about 45 minutes. Add cabbage and cook until tender.

title: fish and clam chowder
directions: Thaw fish if frozen. Cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Chop salt pork. In Dutch oven, cook until brown.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
Set salt pork aside.
Add potatoes, celery and green onion to reserved drippings. Cook until onion is tender.
Add broth. Cover and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add fish and 2 1/2 cups of the milk.
Bring just to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Shake remaining cold milk with flour.
Stir into chowder.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Cook 1 minute more.
Add cream, undrained clams, spinach, pork, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and dash of bottled hot pepper sauce. Serves 8 to 10.

title: tacos
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer on low for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Melt 1 stick butter or oleo and pour over all.
Bake until done, about 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: beggars breakfast
directions: Place cubed bread in greased casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer drained sausage over bread cubes; sprinkle the shredded cheese over sausage.
Combine beaten eggs and milk; pour mixture over ingredients in casserole.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Top with the mayonnaise, sugar and cheese.

title: turtle sundae dessert
directions: Mix cake according to package directions; set aside half of the batter.
Pour remaining batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Meanwhile in a saucepan over low heat, melt the caramels, milk and butter.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Pour reserved batter over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: old english apricot honey bread and muffins
directions: Grease and lightly flour 8 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan or 2 muffin tins. Cream the butter with the honey and add mashed apricots pulp. Beat in egg and juice. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Fold into mixture. Fill loaf pan or muffin tins about half full. Bake loaf in a pre-heated oven at 350° for 45-60 minutes. For muffins, bake for 30-35 minutes in a preheated oven at 375°. Check for doneness with toothpick. Serve hot with honey butter or fresh preserves.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, onions and cheese.
Add Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Sprinkle crushed cheese crackers on top and bake at 350° until crumbs are browned.

title: chicken and wild rice francais
directions: Cook mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine in medium saucepan until tender.
Add water and contents of rice and seasoning packets.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer until all liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
While rice cooks, season chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter or margarine in large skillet.
Add chicken and cook over medium heat until firm and cooked through, 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Lightly saute garlic in drippings.
Add cream, parsley and mustard.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir romaine into rice.
Arrange rice and chicken on serving platter.
Spoon sauce over chicken. Makes about 4 generous servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of boiling water until barely tender and still bright green.
Combine soup and mayonnaise.
Add onions, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. Remove from oven and add cracker crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Drain all the fruit except for the pineapple. Carefully drain pineapple and reserve 2 cups of the pineapple juice. (Sometimes I have to add some of the other fruit juices to make 2 cups.) Mix the pineapple juice with the instant pudding. Whisk until thickened. Add drained fruit and mix well.

title: sweet 'n sour pork or chicken
directions: Cut chicken or pork in pieces.
Brown in pan sprayed with Pam. Reduce heat to low.
Add onion, carrots and green pepper. Combine remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with rice and tossed salad.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pineapple, strawberries and nuts. Put in refrigerator until congealed.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Crush cinnamon snacks and mix in applesauce until desired consistency.
Bake about 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in oil and milk.
Mix in flour and sugar.
Stir just enough to mix.
Add blueberries.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 large or 18 small muffins.

title: tortellini with broccoli and red peppers
directions: Cook tortellini; drain.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add broccoli and red pepper and saute until just tender, about 3 minutes.
Add wine and vinegar and cook 30 seconds.
Add cooked tortellini and toss until heated through, about 1 minute. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add Parmesan cheese to taste.
